#!     <XFORM_PARM PARM_NAME="TEST_DIALOG_PARAMETERS_FOR_RESPONSE" PARM_VALUE="authConnection;&lt;lt&gt;Unused&lt;gt&gt; authEnabled;false authMethod;&lt;lt&gt;Unused&lt;gt&gt; authPassword;&lt;lt&gt;Unused&lt;gt&gt; authUsername;&lt;lt&gt;Unused&lt;gt&gt; contentType;&lt;lt&gt;Unused&lt;gt&gt; method;GET multipartContentType;&lt;lt&gt;Unused&lt;gt&gt; requestHeaders:Accept;application&lt;solidus&gt;octet-stream requestHeaders:Authorization;fmetoken&lt;space&gt;token=3b156e66b0e6d6ced4cd59659ccab48505779818 requestUrl;https:&lt;solidus&gt;&lt;solidus&gt;fme-flow.ddr-stage.services.geo.ca&lt;solidus&gt;fmerest&lt;solidus&gt;v3&lt;solidus&gt;repositories&lt;solidus&gt;PT_Harvester&lt;solidus&gt;items uploadData;&lt;lt&gt;Unused&lt;gt&gt; verifySslCert;Yes version;HTTP_2"/>
#!     <XFORM_PARM PARM_NAME="TEST_DIALOG_RESPONSE_PREVIEW" PARM_VALUE="{ &#9;&quot;items&quot;: [ &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-09T16:12:26-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T12:14:38-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;AB_GEODISCOVER_RESOURCE_EXTRACTOR.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;AB_GEODISCOVER_RESOURCE_EXTRACTOR&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;This custom transformer uses a look-up table with the url of each resources where the list attribute language{} contains the value &apos;fr&apos; and change the value of resources{}.language to &apos;en-fr&apos; for Alberta province in the P/T project of the FGP.&lt;/p&gt; &quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-09T16:13:54-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T11:44:20-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;AB_language_manager.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;AB_language_manager&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuPct&quot;: 82.17245034513974, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuTime&quot;: 1258158, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgElapsedTime&quot;: 1531119, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgPeakMemUsage&quot;: 932771997, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This workbench read and trasform all the metadata for the province of Alberta (AB)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;None&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;None&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_GEO: Flag enabling the processing of the geospatial features. Can take two values: Yes: Process the geospatial features; No: Do not process the geospatial features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_NON_GEO: Flag enabling the processing of the none geospatial features. Can take two values: Yes: Process the none geospatial features; No: Do not process the none geospatial features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_TRANSLATION: Flag enabling the translation of the texts using AWS service. Can take two values: Yes: Translates the texts; No: Do not translate the texts.  The Yes flag can only be used in production mode.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;CATALOGUE_READER_SELECT: Flag enabling the reading of the metadata from the P/T web service. Can take two values: Yes: Read the metadata from the P/T web service; No: Read the metadata from a local source on disk.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;FORCED_PYCSW_URL: URL address of the PYCSW server used to update the metadata.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_FFS_TESTING_FILE: Name of a FFS file containing the metadata records read from the CATALOGUE_READER. This file is used when the parameter: &lt;em&gt;CATALOGUE_READER_SELECT&lt;/em&gt; is set to &lt;em&gt;No&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LOCAL_SOURCE_METADATA_DELTA_FINDER: Flag enabling the use of a local source for the metadata delta finder. Can take two values: Yes: Use a local source as defined by the parameter OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR; No: use the content PyCSW server as defined by the parameter: FORCED_PYCSW_URL.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LOCAL_WRITER: Flag enabling to write the output locally or on the server.  Can take two values: Yes: Write the output locally as defined by the parameter:OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR; No: Write the output in the PyCSW server as defined by the parameter: FORCEDS_PYCSW_URL.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;METADATA_OVERWRITE: Enable the overwite of the PyCSW.  Can take two values: Yes: Overwrite the contentof the PyCSW; No: Do no overwrite the content of the PyCSW.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_OUT_WORKING_DIR: Root working directory used to define the following &lt;em&gt;private parameters&lt;/em&gt;:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;IN_CSV_LOOKUP_TABLES_DIR: Source directory of the root of the lookup table files. Defined as: \\LOOKUP_TABLES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;IN_GMD_XML_TEMPLATES_DIR: Source directory of the root XML templates. Defined as: \\XML_TEMPLATES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;INJSON_TEMPLATE_DIR: Source directory of the root JSON templates. Defined as: \\JSON_TEMPLATES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;LOG_FILE: Output log file. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\LOG\\QC.log&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_JSON_LOCAL_DIR: Source directory to output JSON files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\JSON_LOCAL&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XLS_NOTIFICATION: Source directory to output excel files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XLS&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_FAILED_DIR: Source directory to output failed XML files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XML_FAILED&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR: Source directory to output &lt;em&gt;Local Source&lt;/em&gt; XML files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XML_LOCAL&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_PASSED_DIR: Source directory to output passedXML files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XML_PASSED&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;SAMPLE_SIZE: Number of features to process. Zero (0) means process all the features. A number &lt;em&gt;n&lt;/em&gt; greater than 0 means sample or process only the first &lt;em&gt;n&lt;/em&gt; features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;URL_VALIDATION : Indicates to validate or not created URL. (Should be Yes for prod)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;VALIDATE_INSERT_PCT :Indicates to valide insert percentage. 75 % or less insert/update record  (Should be Yes for prod)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-11T10:48:07-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-11T10:48:06-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;AB_PROD.fmw&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;AB_PROD&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalRuns&quot;: 13, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;WORKSPACE&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This custom Transformer allow the user to set a specified value for one or many attributes into a FME feature (attributes can be simple list i.e. with only one index). It can either overwrite the attribute value or set a specified value if the attribute is Null. The value can be set as text or as another attribute value from the same FME feature. In the case where the specified attribute is a list, the custom Transformer repairs it (it assures there is no missing index into the list). Attributes to process and actions to do are contained into input YAML directives.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;DATA_INPUT : A FME feature.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUTPUT : The FME feature for witch attributes have been modified according the YAML directives.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;IN_YAML_TEXT: YAML directives to determine the attribute and the action to be done on the FME feature. See the section Content of the YAML directives below for a description of the YAML directives.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Content of the YAML directives&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The YAML directives are used by the custom transformer to decide the attribute to process and the process itself. Below is an example of YAML directives. Notice that there is 6 attributes, each of them has 2 keywords values: &lt;em&gt;action&lt;/em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;attr2set&lt;/em&gt; . In YAML syntax dictionnary, the colon must be followed by a SPACE --&amp;gt; action: value .&lt;/p&gt; &lt;pre&gt; notes:&#9; action: attribute_not_null&#9; attr2set: title  iso_topic{}.:&#9; action: attribute_not_null&#9; attr2set: default_iso_topic  publisher:&#9; action: text_overwrite&#9; attr2set: NRCan  description:&#9; action: text_not_null&#9; attr2set: Description PGF  maintainer:&#9; action: attribute_overwrite&#9; attr2set: description  tags{}.name:&#9; action: attribute_not_null&#9; attr2set: default_tags_display_name &lt;/pre&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description of the YAML directives&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The first part of the YAML is the name of the FME attribute on which we want to do an action, it can be a list with a specific attribute to access (e.g. &lt;em&gt;iso_topic{}.topic_value&lt;/em&gt; ) or just a list (e.g.&lt;em&gt; iso_topic{}.&lt;/em&gt; ). Note that if the FME feature being processed does not contain the specific attribute of the list you want to access, it will not be process. For example, if you want to do text_not_null on every feature for the list _ iso_topic {}.&lt;em&gt;,you need to specify the specific attribute of the list (_topic_value&lt;/em&gt;) so that all feature will be affected, even those not containing &lt;em&gt;iso_topic{}.topic_value&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;When referring to a list, it is important to write it with the following 3 characters \&quot;&lt;em&gt;{}.&lt;/em&gt;\&quot;. It can also be a single attribute (e.g. &lt;em&gt;description&lt;/em&gt; ).&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Following the FME attribute to process, there are 2 keywords: &lt;em&gt;action&lt;/em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;attr2set&lt;/em&gt; . The keyword action defines the action to do with the attribute it relates to, 4 options are available. The keyword &lt;em&gt;attr2set&lt;/em&gt; , defines either the attribute name or a text literal depending of the action selected. If the action name contains &lt;em&gt;attribute&lt;/em&gt; , then it sets the value of the specified attribute. If the action name contains &lt;em&gt;text&lt;/em&gt; then it sets the text written.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;action :&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;attribute_not_null&lt;/em&gt;: This option verify if the attribute value is &lt;em&gt;Null&lt;/em&gt; , if yes it sets the value of the attribute specified by the &lt;em&gt;attr2set&lt;/em&gt; keyword.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;attribute_overwrite&lt;/em&gt;: This option overwrite the attribute value by setting the value of the attribute specified by the &lt;em&gt;attr2set&lt;/em&gt; keyword.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;text_not_null&lt;/em&gt;: This option verify if the attribute value is &lt;em&gt;Null&lt;/em&gt; , if yes it sets the text written into the &lt;em&gt;attr2set&lt;/em&gt; keyword.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;text_overwrite&lt;/em&gt;: This option overwrite the attribute value, it sets the text written into the &lt;em&gt;attr2set&lt;/em&gt; keyword.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;attr2set:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;attribute_not_null&lt;/em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;attribute_overwrite&lt;/em&gt;: Sets the attribute value specified.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;text_not_null&lt;/em&gt; and &lt;em&gt;text_overwrite&lt;/em&gt;: Sets the literal text written.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;New attributes or list:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;If the list or the attribute written into the YAML does not exist, it will be created. Lists will be set with an index &lt;em&gt;{0}&lt;/em&gt;. Note that attributes or lists are processed in the YAML from top to bottom. Sometimes, it may be usefull to use 2 times the Custom Transformer to do many process on the same attribute.&lt;/p&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:10-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T11:45:01-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;ATTRIBUTE_MANAGER_NG.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;ATTRIBUTE_MANAGER_NG&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This custom transformer edits (maps) values specified in an input file to a specified attribute. It also checks the number of characters of this attribute to a specified value. It output through the TO_LONG port the features for wich the attribute is to long and and not mapped. The specified attribute can be a list or not. It uses the METADATA_VALUE_MAPPER_NG custom transformer for which the description is below.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;DATA_INPUT: The input metadata records to process.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;CORRECT_LENGTH: The processed output metadata records with value mapped and attribute length verified.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;TOO_LONG: The processed output metdata records value mapped and for wich the attribute length is to long.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_ATT_TO_MAP: Name of the attribute on wich the mapping and the length verification needs to be done. It can be a list attribute or not.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_CHAR_LIMIT: Number of characters over wich the attribute will be compare (smaller or equal to).&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;METADATA_VALUE_MAPPER_NG params: See next section&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;hr /&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;p style=\&quot;text-align: center;\&quot;&gt;METADATA_VALUE_MAPPER_NG &lt;/p&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This custom transformer edits (maps) values to valid English values (if requested) and valid French values equivalent (if requested) and value code RI_CODES (if requested).  The name of the attribute to map and French, English and RI_CODES action are parametrizable.  &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Note: If the attribute ou attribute list is not present on the feature an error is created.  If the element to map is not present in the lookup table an error is created.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;DATA_INPUT: The input metadata records to process.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUTPUT: The process output metdata records with value mapped.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ATT_TO_MAP: Name of the FME attribute or FME list attribute to map in plain text (ex.: &apos;format&apos; or &apos;resources{}.format&apos;).  Do not use the Open Text Editor &amp;gt; FME Feature Attribute option to select the attribute to map;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ERROR_NOT_MAPPED: Flag use to map data values that cannot be found in the loopup tables. Can take 2 values: Yes: map data values not found; No: Do not map data values not found;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ENGLISH_REFRESH: Flag use for updating English attribute value. Can take two value: Yes: update English attribute value; No do not update English attribute value;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;FRENCH_REFRESH: Flag use for creating or updating French attribute value. Can take two value: Yes: update French attribute value; No do not update French atribute value;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;CODE_REFRESH: Flag use for creating updating the RI_CODES. Can take two value: Yes: update the code; No do not update the code;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;FEATURE_TYPE: Name of the CSV file to read (without .csv extension);&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_CSV_LOOKUP_TABLES_DIR: Name of the directory path containing the CSV file to read;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;P-T_ABBR: Two letters abbreviation of the province or the territory.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:10-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T11:45:18-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;ATTRIBUTE_MAPPER_AND_LENGTH_CHECKER.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;ATTRIBUTE_MAPPER_AND_LENGTH_CHECKER&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This custom transformer cleans all string attributes by performing the followin tasks: &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Remove html directive (ex.: &lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;bla bla bla &amp;lt;\\p&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;) so that the string contains only plain text&#9;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Replace special character (carriage return, line feed, tab) by white spaces&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Replace curly braces {} by parenthesis&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Removing front and trailing white spaces&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Replace multiple white spaces by only one white space&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;INPUT: The input metadata records to clean&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;OUTPUT: The cleaned output metdata records&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;None&lt;/p&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:11-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T11:48:48-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;ATTRIBUTE_VALUE_TEXT_CLEANER_NG.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;ATTRIBUTE_VALUE_TEXT_CLEANER_NG&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T13:21:03-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T11:56:42-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;BC_CONTACTS_MANAGER.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;BC_CONTACTS_MANAGER&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuPct&quot;: 76.27591617668692, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuTime&quot;: 855545, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgElapsedTime&quot;: 1121645, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgPeakMemUsage&quot;: 762187776, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This workbench read and trasform all the metadata for the province of British Columbia (BC)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;None&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;None&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_GEO: Flag enabling the processing of the geospatial features. Can take two values: Yes: Process the geospatial features; No: Do not process the geospatial features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_NON_GEO: Flag enabling the processing of the none geospatial features. Can take two values: Yes: Process the none geospatial features; No: Do not process the none geospatial features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_TRANSLATION: Flag enabling the translation of the texts using AWS service. Can take two values: Yes: Translates the texts; No: Do not translate the texts.  The Yes flag can only be used in production mode.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;CATALOGUE_READER_SELECT: Flag enabling the reading of the metadata from the P/T web service. Can take two values: Yes: Read the metadata from the P/T web service; No: Read the metadata from a local source on disk.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;FORCED_PYCSW_URL: URL address of the PYCSW server used to update the metadata.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_FFS_TESTING_FILE: Name of a FFS file containing the metadata records read from the CATALOGUE_READER. This file is used when the parameter: &lt;em&gt;CATALOGUE_READER_SELECT&lt;/em&gt; is set to &lt;em&gt;No&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LOCAL_SOURCE_METADATA_DELTA_FINDER: Flag enabling the use of a local source for the metadata delta finder. Can take two values: Yes: Use a local source as defined by the parameter OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR; No: use the content PyCSW server as defined by the parameter: FORCED_PYCSW_URL.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LOCAL_WRITER: Flag enabling to write the output locally or on the server.  Can take two values: Yes: Write the output locally as defined by the parameter:OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR; No: Write the output in the PyCSW server as defined by the parameter: FORCEDS_PYCSW_URL.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;METADATA_OVERWRITE: Enable the overwite of the PyCSW.  Can take two values: Yes: Overwrite the contentof the PyCSW; No: Do no overwrite the content of the PyCSW.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_OUT_WORKING_DIR: Root working directory used to define the following &lt;em&gt;private parameters&lt;/em&gt;:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;IN_CSV_LOOKUP_TABLES_DIR: Source directory of the root of the lookup table files. Defined as: \\LOOKUP_TABLES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;IN_GMD_XML_TEMPLATES_DIR: Source directory of the root XML templates. Defined as: \\XML_TEMPLATES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;INJSON_TEMPLATE_DIR: Source directory of the root JSON templates. Defined as: \\JSON_TEMPLATES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;LOG_FILE: Output log file. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\LOG\\QC.log&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_JSON_LOCAL_DIR: Source directory to output JSON files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\JSON_LOCAL&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XLS_NOTIFICATION: Source directory to output excel files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XLS&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_FAILED_DIR: Source directory to output failed XML files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XML_FAILED&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR: Source directory to output &lt;em&gt;Local Source&lt;/em&gt; XML files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XML_LOCAL&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_PASSED_DIR: Source directory to output passedXML files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XML_PASSED&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;SAMPLE_SIZE: Number of features to process. Zero (0) means process all the features. A number &lt;em&gt;n&lt;/em&gt; greater than 0 means sample or process only the first &lt;em&gt;n&lt;/em&gt; features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;URL_VALIDATION : Indicates to validate or not created URL. (Should be Yes for prod)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;VALIDATE_INSERT_PCT :Indicates to valide insert percentage. 75 % or less insert/update record  (Should be Yes for prod)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-02-27T13:05:27-05:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2026-02-27T13:05:26-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;BC_PROD.fmw&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;BC_PROD&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalRuns&quot;: 14, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;WORKSPACE&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:12-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-10-06T14:59:14-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;BC_WMS_FORMATTER.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;BC_WMS_FORMATTER&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This Custom Transformer enables to read a CKAN or a CSW server and extract the requested metadata records.  Once the metadata records are extracted, they are transformed from their hierarchcal structure (JSON for CKAN and XML for CSW) into a flattened FME attribute and list features.  The parameters allow great flexibility on how the CKAN or CSW server are requested.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Note: No modification other then the JSON/XML flattening is performed on the metadata records read from the CKAN/CSW server.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Input: One feature to signal the start of the metadata server extraction.&#9;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Résultats: The features resulting from the CKAN or the CSW server extraction.  One output feature for each metadata record read.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Métadonnées invalides: Used to output ID not found in the CKAN or CSW server. On ly used when the parameter &lt;em&gt;IDENTIFIANT&lt;/em&gt; is used.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;UUID_invalide: Used when the ID is not a valid UUID. On ly used when the parameter &lt;em&gt;IDENTIFIANT&lt;/em&gt; is used.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;SOURCE_URL: The source URL (web address) of the target CKAN or CSW server. There are 6 pre-defined source url and one user defined address (drop down bix):&lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;FGP-STAGING_INTERNE: Address of the external internal FGP staging server;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;FGP-STAGING-EXTERNE:Address of the internal internal FGP staging server;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;FGP-PROD_INTERNE: Address of the internal FGP production server ;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;FGP-PROD-EXTERNE: Address of the externall FGP production server;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OPENDATA-STAGING: Address of the Open Data staging server;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OPENDATA-PROD: Address of the Open Data production server;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;PYCSW-INTERNAL: Address of the internal PYCSW server;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;CUSTOM-CSW/CKAN: Custom URL address of a CKAN or CSW server to be supplied by the user in the &lt;em&gt;CUSTOM_URL&lt;/em&gt; parameter.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;CUSTOM_URL: The address of the server to be used when &lt;em&gt;CUSTOM-CSW/CKAN&lt;/em&gt; option is choosen with &lt;em&gt;SOURCE_URL&lt;/em&gt; parameter. &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;CKAN_FILER: String to be used with CKAN server to filter the result. Ex.: fq=collection:fgp where &lt;em&gt;fq&lt;/em&gt; is the CKAN reserved word for filtering, &lt;em&gt;collection&lt;/em&gt; is a the name of a key in the JSON document and &lt;em&gt;fgp&lt;/em&gt; is the requested value for the filtering;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;CUSTOM_CSW_SCHEMA: Drop down box specifying the output schema to use to generate the metadata records (default: http://www.iso tc211.org/2005/ gmd). Used with CSW server.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;CUSTOM_CSW_VERSION: Drop down box specifying the version of the CSW server to use (default: 2.0.2)&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;CUSTOM_URL_CSW_TYPENAMES: Dropdown box specifying which entities must be queried from the information model (default: gmd:MD_Met adata). Used with CSW server.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;CUSTOM_CSW_LIST_NAME: Dropdown box specifying the name of the FME list attribute used to explode the list attribute . (fefault MD_Metadata{}) Used with CSW server.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;IDENTIFIANT:  UUID identifying the ID of the metadata record to extract from the server. Used with CSW and CKAN server.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;CUSTOM_URL_BY_ID_ATT_NAME:&lt;em&gt; Not used any more&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;CSW_ANY_TEXT_FILTER: A string to be used to filter the metadata records.  Any string canbe used.  can filter any field of the metadata record.  Used with CSW server. &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note&lt;/strong&gt;:  For more information on the use of the parameters of the CSW server, refer to the official OGC documentation &lt;a href=\&quot;https://portal.opengeospatial.org/files/?artifact_id=77949\&quot;&gt; OGC PDF documentation&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:13-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T12:08:47-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;Catalogue_Reader_YT_CKAN.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;Catalogue Reader_YT_CKAN&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:13-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-06T15:26:23-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;COMPARATEUR_JSON.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;COMPARATEUR_JSON&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:14-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-07T12:35:55-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;COMPARATEUR_JSON_3.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;COMPARATEUR_JSON_3&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:14-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-06T15:26:23-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;COMPARATEUR_XML.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;COMPARATEUR_XML&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:14-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-07T12:35:12-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;COMPARATEUR_XML_PYTHON_SYS_EXIT.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;COMPARATEUR_XML_PYTHON_SYS_EXIT&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This Custom Transformer is used to read ESRI GeoHub DCAT server.  GeoHub DCAT reader is using two server extractions (a primary and a secondary) to extract a complete set of DCAT metadata for each record.  Metadata extracted from the primary server extracttion are prefixed wirh &lt;em&gt;DCAT_P&lt;/em&gt; whereas the the metadata extracted from the secondary server extraction are prefixed with &lt;em&gt;DCAT_S&lt;/em&gt;.  In order to join the metadata from the primary and the secondary extraction both extraction must share a common identifier when no common identifier are found the is no secondary metadata with the prfix &lt;em&gt;DCAT_S&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Note: There is no option to read only one record with a specific identifier.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Input: One feature to start the extraction of all the records from the GeoHub DCAT server.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Résultats: All the records read from the GeoHub DCAT server.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;GEO_HUB_SERVICE: Name of the DCAT servers to use. Choices are:&lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Manitoba GeoHub: To read Manitoba GeoHub;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Saskatchewan GeoHub: To read Sakatchewan GeoHub;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Custom GeoHub: To enter specific values of primary and secondary url;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;CUSTOM_PRIMARY: Definition of the primary Geo Hub service. Used when the option &lt;em&gt;Custom GeoHub&lt;/em&gt; is selected;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;CUSTOM_SECONDARY: Definition of the seconary Geo Hub service. Used when the option &lt;em&gt;Custom GeoHub&lt;/em&gt; is selected.  It is possible to leave this field empty, in that case no secondary service will be read and less metadata will be extracted.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:15-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T12:10:27-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;DCAT_Reader_MB_SK.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;DCAT_Reader_MB_SK&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This Custom Transformer is used to read ESRI GeoHub DCAT server.  GeoHub DCAT reader is using two server extractions (a primary and a secondary) to extract a complete set of DCAT metadata for each record.  Metadata extracted from the primary server extracttion are prefixed wirh &lt;em&gt;DCAT_P&lt;/em&gt; whereas the the metadata extracted from the secondary server extraction are prefixed with &lt;em&gt;DCAT_S&lt;/em&gt;.  In order to join the metadata from the primary and the secondary extraction both extraction must share a common identifier when no common identifier are found the is no secondary metadata with the prfix &lt;em&gt;DCAT_S&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Note: There is no option to read only one record with a specific identifier.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Input: One feature to start the extraction of all the records from the GeoHub DCAT server.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Résultats: All the records read from the GeoHub DCAT server.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;GEO_HUB_SERVICE: Name of the DCAT servers to use. Choices are:&lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Manitoba GeoHub: To read Manitoba GeoHub;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Saskatchewan GeoHub: To read Sakatchewan GeoHub;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Custom GeoHub: To enter specific values of primary and secondary url;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;CUSTOM_PRIMARY: Definition of the primary Geo Hub service. Used when the option &lt;em&gt;Custom GeoHub&lt;/em&gt; is selected;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;CUSTOM_SECONDARY: Definition of the seconary Geo Hub service. Used when the option &lt;em&gt;Custom GeoHub&lt;/em&gt; is selected.  It is possible to leave this field empty, in that case no secondary service will be read and less metadata will be extracted.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:15-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T12:16:59-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;DCAT_Reader_PEI.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;DCAT_Reader_PEI&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This custom transformer maps each value pair (key, value) from the lookup table as attribute into each metadata record. If there are 25 value pairs in the lookup table each metadata records will have 25 new attributes. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;DATA_INPUT: The input metadata records to process.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUTPUT: The process output metdata records with new attributes (key, value).&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;FEATURE_TYPE: Name of the CSV file to read (without .csv extension);&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_CSV_LOOKUP_TABLES_DIR: Name of the directory path containing the CSV file to read;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;P-T_ABBR: Two letters abbreviation of the province or the territory.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:16-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T12:17:26-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;DEFAULT_ATTRIBUTE_MAPPER_NG.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;DEFAULT_ATTRIBUTE_MAPPER_NG&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This custom transformer identifies and removes duplicate Web services based on the protocol and xlink_role attributes. If duplicate services are found the protocol and xlink_role attributes are reset.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;INPUT: Input metadata records toprocess&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUTPUT: The process output metdata records with resources validated&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;NONE&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:16-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T12:28:45-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;DUPLICATE_SERVICE_REMOVER.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;DUPLICATE_SERVICE_REMOVER&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This custom transformer corrects wrongly formed email addresses.  It manages two cases: firstly when the email address do not contain the character\&quot;@\&quot;, the email address is replaced by the default email adress; secondly when addresses are separated by coma, the email addresses are separated and placed into independant list of contacts{}.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;INPUT: The input metadata records to process.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUTPUT: The process output metadata records with email addresses corrected.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;DEFAULT_CONTACT_EMAIL: Name of the attribute containing the default email address or string character representing the default email address&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:16-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T12:32:16-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;EMAIL_FORMAT_TESTER.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;EMAIL_FORMAT_TESTER&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Custom transformer utilisé pour extraire une étendue temporelle lorsque possible dans une chaine de caractère. Le custom a 3 actions possibles à poser.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ol&gt; &lt;li&gt;Si la chaine de caractère est vide, on attribue la date de début à 0001-01-01. La date de fin est vide &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Si la chaine de caractère match une des expression régulière définies dans le code, le programme extrait la date de début et aussi de fin lorque présente &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;Si la chaine de caractère ne matche pas l&apos;expression régulière, il est possibile de définir manuellement les valeurs de début/fin grâce à une lookup table&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ol&gt; &lt;p&gt;Dans le cas où aucune des trois actions n&apos;est possible, la feature ressort par le port unworking_extraction. Dans ce cas, on doit mettre à jour la lookup table ou bien ajouter une regex dans le code python.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Définifition de la lookup table:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;On utilise une lookup table selon template yaml suivant:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;pre&gt; CSV_COLUMNS:  source_date_extent: [trim, no_null]  data_collection_start_date: [trim, no_null]  data_collection_end_date: [trim]   # CREATE_KEY_VALUE: # NO_DUPLICATE: DUP_1: [source_date_extent] # CHECK_DOMAIN: &lt;/pre&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Lorsque l&apos;extraction fonctionne, on ajoute les attributs data_collection_start_date et data_collection_end_date. Lorsque ça ne fonctionne pas, l&apos;attribut unmatched_date_extent contient la chaine de caractère non matchée.&lt;/p&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:17-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T12:33:46-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;EXTRACT_COLLECTION_START_END_DATE.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;EXTRACT_COLLECTION_START_END_DATE&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:17-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-03T14:49:29-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;EXTRACT_C_DATA_TEMP.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;EXTRACT_C_DATA_TEMP&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;Capture FFS from transformers&lt;/p&gt; &quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:18-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-09-24T14:49:05-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;FFS_CAPTURE.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;FFS_CAPTURE&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;Capture FFS from transformers&lt;/p&gt; &quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:18-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-09-24T14:31:41-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;FFS_CaptureHarness.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;FFS_CaptureHarness&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This custom transformer validates and corrects resources when the format is WMS.  when the format is WMS the URL must contained the following substring \&quot;service=wms\&quot; otherwise the format is set to \&quot;other\&quot;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;INPUT: The input metadata records to process.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUTPUT: The process output metdata records with the format validated.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;NONE&lt;/p&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:18-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T12:34:06-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;FORMAT_VALIDATOR.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;FORMAT_VALIDATOR&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This custom transformer edits (maps) values specified in an input file to a specified attribute and then detect the language for that specified attribute on other features that haven&apos;t been mapped. More precisely, if mapping of the attribute is done, the custom transformer adds  an underscore ( _en or _fr) according to language it is mapped to. Otherwise, the language detection is made. The custom transformer outputs the attributes language_detected, translation_mode and attr_to_translate which are usefull as input into the AWS_TRANSLATE transformer. When langage detection is made, it also output _sum_lang and _sum_lang_stats which are attributes related to FRENCH_ENGLISH_LANGUAGE_DETECT cutom transformer.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;It uses the METADATA_VALUE_MAPPER_NG and FRENCH_ENGLISH_LANGUAGE_DETECT customs transformers for which the description is available inside both transformers.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;DATA_INPUT: The input metadata records to process.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; CSV file description &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;It is important to consider quote (\&quot; \&quot;) and end of the line character (ex: \\r\\n) in the csv file in order to obtain a successfull mapping.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;original_value: The original value to map.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;real_value_english : The English value to set.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;real_value_french: The French value to set.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;code_value: The language of the textmapped (Bilingual, French, English)&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;No_Detection: Features for wich no language detection was made on the specified attribute. The 2 attributes _sum_lang and _sum_lang_stats can be usefull in order to map the specified attribute correctly.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;Check_Lang: Features for wich a language other than French or English was detected. The 2 attributes _sum_lang and _sum_lang_stats can be usefull in order to map the specified attribute correctly.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;Bilingual: Features for wich French or English was detected. The 2 attributes _sum_lang and _sum_lang_stats can be usefull in order to map the specified attribute correctly.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;Processed: Feature for wich language detection was done correctly. The 2 attributes _sum_lang and _sum_lang_stats can be usefull to validate the detection.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ATTR_2_TRANSLATE: Name of the FME attribute to map and translate in plain text (ex.: &apos;notes&apos;).  Do not use the Open Text Editor &amp;gt; FME Feature Attribute option to select the attribute to map.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ATTR_2_TRANSLATE_CODE: Name of the FME attribute to map and translate with &apos;_code&apos; (ex.: &apos;notes_code&apos;). This attribute is needed to store the &apos;code_value&apos; mapped from the csv file. Do not use the Open Text Editor &amp;gt; FME Feature Attribute option to select the attribute to map.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ATT_TO_MAP: Name of the FME attribute to map in plain text (ex.: &apos;notes&apos;).  Do not use the Open Text Editor &amp;gt; FME Feature Attribute option to select the attribute to map.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ERROR_NOT_MAPPED: Flag use to map data values that cannot be found in the loopup tables. Can take 2 values: Yes: map data values not found; No: Do not map data values not found; Hardcoded to YES for the purpose of this transformer.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ENGLISH_REFRESH: Flag use for updating English attribute value. Can take two value: Yes: update English attribute value; No do not update English attribute value;  Hardcoded to YES for the purpose of this transformer.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;FRENCH_REFRESH: Flag use for creating or updating French attribute value. Can take two value: Yes: update French attribute value; No do not update French atribute value;  Hardcoded to YES for the purpose of this transformer.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;CODE_REFRESH: Flag use for creating updating the RI_CODES. Can take two value: Yes: update the code; No do not update the code;  Hardcoded to YES for the purpose of this transformer.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;FEATURE_TYPE: Name of the CSV file to read (without .csv extension);&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_CSV_LOOKUP_TABLES_DIR: Name of the directory path containing the CSV file to read;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;P-T_ABBR: Two letters abbreviation of the province or the territory.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:19-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T12:34:48-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;FRENCH_ENGLISH_LANGUAGE_DETECT_AND_MAPPING.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;FRENCH_ENGLISH_LANGUAGE_DETECT_AND_MAPPING&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This custom transformer is doing 2 tasks. Firstly, it creates and validates that the web link is well formed, online and responding; Secondly it is adding a new ressources{} attribute list containing the web link and the other information contained in the CSV file.  Unvalid web links are log in the FME logger.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Note: The web link to test is build from the &lt;em&gt;default key&lt;/em&gt; &lt;strong&gt;url&lt;/strong&gt; contained in the CSV and the attribute value from the &lt;em&gt;WEBLINK_WILDCARD&lt;/em&gt; parameter.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;DATA_INPUT: The input metadata records to process.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUTPUT: The process output metdata records with the added web link resource.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;WEBLINK_WILDCARD: Name of the attribute containing the information to add to the web link in order to retreive the metadata record from the P-T portal&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;URL_VALIDATION: Flag use to validate if the web link is well formed, online and responding. Can take 2 values: YES: validate the web link; NO: Do not validate th web link. Note: During testing, it is interesting to use NO as the validation is very slow;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;FEATURE_TYPE: Name of the CSV file to read (without .csv extension);&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_CSV_LOOKUP_TABLES_DIR: Name of the directory path containing the CSV file to read;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;P-T_ABBR: Two letters abbreviation of the province or the territory.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:19-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T12:35:55-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;GEOPORTAL_WEBLINK_ADDER_NG.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;GEOPORTAL_WEBLINK_ADDER_NG&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This custom transformer will add spatial extents to metadata records that do not have spatial extents.  For the matadata records without a spatial extent, the spatial extents are extracted from a lookup table based on the location attribute of the metadata record.  If the spatial extent is not set and the location is not present in the lookup table the spatial extent cannot be set and a description is added in the log file.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;INPUT: The input metadata records to process.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;EXTENT_DEFINED: The output metdata records for which the spatial extent is defined (already present and/or added).&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;UNKNOWN_EXTENT: The output metdata records for which the spatial extent is unknown (not defined).&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LATITUDE_MIN: Minimum latitude for all the entries of the lookup table;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LATITUDE_MAX: Maximum latitude for all the entries of the lookup table;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LONGITUDE_MIN: Minimum longitude for all the entries of the lookup table;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LONGITUDE_MAX: Maximum longitude for all the entries of the lookup table;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;FEATURE_TYPE: Name of the CSV file to read (without .csv extension);&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_CSV_LOOKUP_TABLES_DIR: Name of the directory path containing the CSV file to read;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;P-T_ABBR: Two letters abbreviation of the province or the territory.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:20-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T12:35:09-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;GEO_EXTENTS_MAPPER_NG.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;GEO_EXTENTS_MAPPER_NG&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This custom transformer fans out the metadata records between two types of metadata (GeoSpatial and None GeoSpatial). When a metadata record cannot be validates as GeoSpatial it is declared None Geospatial. In order to determine the type of metadata record, the transformer analyse attributes according to the YAML directives. See the section Content of the YAML directives below for a complete description of the YAML directives.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This custom transformer also adds the attribute _&lt;em&gt;typedatasets&lt;/em&gt; which contains the value &lt;em&gt;geo&lt;/em&gt; for the geospatial features and &lt;em&gt;nonegeo&lt;/em&gt; for the none geospatial features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;DATA_INPUT: The input metadata records to process.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;GEOSPATIAL: Output port for all gepspatial metadata records;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;NON-GEOSPATIAL: Output port for all none geospatial metadata records;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;ERROR_LOG: Output port for metadata records that need to be logged according to the YAML directives.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;Note: All the input records will go through either the GeoSpatial the None GeoSpatial port. Some input records may be duplicated and sent through the LOG_ERROR port if requested by the YAML directives.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;CSV_FILE_NAME: Name lookup table file name in CSV format. &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;CSV_PATH: File path of the CSV file. &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;CSV_PROVINCE: Code of the province (two letters) . &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;YAML_DIRECTIVES: YAML directives for determining the Geospatial and None Geospatial records. See the section Content of the YAML directives below for a description of the YAML directives.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;Content of the YAML directives &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The YAML directives are used by the custom transformer to decide the type of the metadata records: GeoSpatial or None GeoSpatial. Here&apos;s an exemple of a YAML directives:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;pre&gt; resources{}.format:   domain: lookup_table_format   spatial_type: overwrite   not_found: log   search_type: equals   #   description:   domain: [spatial, geographic]   spatial_type: no_overwrite   not_found: no_log   search_type: contains  &lt;/pre&gt;  &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description of the YAML directives&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The first part of the YAML is the name of the FME attribute to use to validate the record, it can be a list attribute (ex.: resources{}..format) or a simple attribute (ex.: description). If it&apos;s a list attribute,the name must contain the 2 characters:\&quot;{}\&quot;. The content of that attribute will be used to determine if the record is GeoSpatial or None GeoSpatial.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Following the FME attribute to validate, there are 4 keywords: domain, spatial_type, not_found and search_type.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The first keyword domain defines the domain of values that are used to determine if a metadata record is GeoSpatial or None GeoSpatial. Two values are possible: lookup_table_format or a list of word defining the domain between brackets (ex.: [point, line, poygone]). When using the keyword lookup_table_format, the custom transformer will use the content of the column name format of the CSV fileto define the domain of values. The record type will be GeoSpatial if the column fgp_publish is set to \&quot;oui\&quot;. When using a domain list, the metadata record will be GeoSpatial if the value of the FME attribute is contained in the domain list.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The second keyword spatial_type defines how to set the spatial type when there is a domain match of the FME attribute. Three values are possible: no_overwite, overwrite and if_null_overwrite. no_overwite means that even if there is a match do not try to overwrite the spatial type. overwite means that if there is a match, take the spatial type value associated in the CSV file (column name: spatial_type) and assign it (or create it if empty) to the corresponding FME attribute. if_null_overwite as the same meaning as overwrite but only when the content of the spatial type is empty or missing. The values overwrite and if_null_overwrite can only be used when the domain keyword value is lookup_table_format.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The third keyword not_found defines how the custom transformer behaves when an FME attribute is not found in the domain of values. Two values are possible: log and no_log. log means create a duplicate (clone) of the record and send it through the LOG_ERROR output port. no_log means do not log any error when the FME attribute is not found in the domain of values.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;The fourth keyword search type defines how to search the content of the FME attribute. Two values are possible: equals or contains. equals means that the value of the FME attribute must be exactly the same. contains means that one of the word the FME attribute must be in the domain values (usefull when we search for one word in a sentence).&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;You can define more than one FME attribute to search. Do not duplicate the FME attribute name because the last one will overwrite the others.&lt;/p&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:20-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T12:35:29-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;GEO_NONE_GEO_SELECTOR.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;GEO_NONE_GEO_SELECTOR&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This transformer copies original lists then removes duplicates from elements where only unique values are required for the dataset.  Duplicate attribute format are removed. Duplicate projection name are removed. Only the first occurrence of the cycle and cycle_code attributes are kept. Duplicate more_info{}.link are removed&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;INPUT: Input metadata records to process.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;DATA_OUTPUT: The process output metdata records.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;NONE&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:20-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T12:36:25-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;GMD_SECTION_DATA_EXTRACTION.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;GMD_SECTION_DATA_EXTRACTION&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This custom transformer is translating the input CKAN metadata model into the JSON TBS model.  The rules on how to map the input CKAN features attributes into the TBS attributes are stored in the JSON configuration file. The JSON templates used to create the JSON file are supplied with the input parameters of the custom transformers.  The mapping into JSON file is done with FME JSON Templater transformer.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Input: The input metadata records to translate into the JSON TBS model.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUTPUT_LOCAL: The output metdata records translated into the JSON TBS model.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;JSON_ROOT_TEMPLATE: File system address containing the root section of the TBS model in JSON format.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;JSON_RESOURCE_TEMPLATE: File system address containing the resources section of the TBS model in JSON format.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:21-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T12:36:59-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;JSON_PUBLISHER_NG.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;JSON_PUBLISHER_NG&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This custom transformer allows to sort the metadata records based on the type of license.  If the licence allows to publish the metadata records in the FGP, the metadata records  are sent to the LICENSE_FILTER_PASSED port.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;DATA_INPUT: The input metadata records to process.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LICENSE_FILTER_PASSED: The metadata records that have a license allowing to be publish in the FGP;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LICENSE_FILTER_UNPASSED: The metadata records that &lt;strong&gt;do not&lt;/strong&gt; have a license allowing to be publish in the FGP;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;UNKNOWN_LICENCE: The metadata records with a license not found in the lookup table.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LICENCE_ATT: Name of the attribute of the metadata record containing the licence type used to determine if the metadata records can be published in the FGP;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;FEATURE_TYPE: The name of the CSV file containing the information on the licensing;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_CSV_LOOKUP_TABLES_DIR: The path to the directory containing the CSV file;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;P-T_ABBR: Two letters abbreviation of the province or territory&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:21-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T12:38:52-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;LICENSE_FILTER_NG.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;LICENSE_FILTER_NG&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;Replaces the specified source list with the same name list containing only elements that match the specified condition. If the source list does not contain matched elements at all, the input feature will be output via the NotFound port without any change.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;This transformer performs filtering with one of these filter types.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;---------- &lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; color:#aa0000;\&quot;&gt;Has Value&lt;/span&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;: Every element in the resulting list stores a value (i.e. non-empty, non-null, non-missing).&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; color:#aa0000;\&quot;&gt;Exact Match&lt;/span&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;: Every element in the resulting list stores a value that exact matches the specified string.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; color:#aa0000;\&quot;&gt;Contains&lt;/span&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;: Every element in the resulting list stores a value that contains the specified string.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; color:#aa0000;\&quot;&gt;Begins With&lt;/span&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;: Every element in the resulting list stores a value that begins with the specified string.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; color:#aa0000;\&quot;&gt;Ends With&lt;/span&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;: Every element in the resulting list stores a value that ends with the specified string.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; color:#aa0000;\&quot;&gt;Regular Expression Match&lt;/span&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;: Every element in the resulting list stores a value that matches the specified regular expression.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; color:#aa0000;\&quot;&gt;Numeric Value&lt;/span&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;: Every element in the resulting list stores a numeric value.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; color:#aa0000;\&quot;&gt;Numeric Range&lt;/span&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;: Every element in the resulting list stores a numeric value within the specified range.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;---------- &lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; font-size:medium; color:#000000;\&quot;&gt;This transformer treats a null and missing element as an empty string when determining if an element matches the filtering condition&lt;/span&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; font-size:medium; color:#000000;\&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;However, a null or missing element will be propagated to the resulting list as is, if it matches the filtering condition.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;This transformer supports simple lists (e.g. _list{}) and structured lists (e.g. _list{}.foo, _list{}.bar), but doesn&apos;t support nested lists (e.g. _list{}.sub{}).&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;If a member (component) of a structured list is specified as the source, other members (components) of the same list will also be filtered synchronously with the specified member.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;This transformer differentiates a simple list and structured list having the same base name. For example, when \&quot;_base{}\&quot; is specified as the source, \&quot;_base{}.foo\&quot; and \&quot;_base{}.bar\&quot; won&apos;t be processed even though the base name is the same as the source list. Vice versa. &lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;If the filtering cannot be performed with an unexpected reason (e.g. malformed regular expression), the input feature will be output via the &amp;lt;Rejected&amp;gt; port, and the rejected features will have an attribute named \&quot;_rejected_reason\&quot; that stores a string describing the rejected reason.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; font-weight:600; color:#0000ff;\&quot;&gt;Example&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;Consider that the input feature has this list - contains 5 elements, index range is 0 to 4.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; color:#aa0000;\&quot;&gt;_list{}.foo = [1,2,3,4,5]&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; color:#aa0000;\&quot;&gt;_list{}.bar = [a,b,c,d,e]&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;If you set the parameters like this:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;- Source List Attribute: &lt;/span&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; color:#aa0000;\&quot;&gt;_list{}.foo&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;- Filter Type: &lt;/span&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; color:#aa0000;\&quot;&gt;Numeric Range&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;- Match Expression: &lt;/span&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; color:#aa0000;\&quot;&gt;(2,5)&lt;/span&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; font-style:italic; color:#333333;\&quot;&gt;this expression represents \&quot;greater than 2 and less than 5\&quot;&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;the resulting list will be:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; color:#aa0000;\&quot;&gt;_list{}.foo = [3,4]&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; color:#aa0000;\&quot;&gt;_list{}.bar = [c,d]&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;Here, the number of the resulting elements is 2 and the index range is 0 to 1.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:22-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T12:39:17-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;ListElementFilter.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;ListElementFilter&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuPct&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuTime&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgElapsedTime&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgPeakMemUsage&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This workbench read and trasform all the metadata for the province of NewFoundLand &amp;amp; Labrador (NL)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;None&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;None&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_GEO: Flag enabling the processing of the geospatial features. Can take two values: Yes: Process the geospatial features; No: Do not process the geospatial features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_NON_GEO: Flag enabling the processing of the none geospatial features. Can take two values: Yes: Process the none geospatial features; No: Do not process the none geospatial features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_TRANSLATION: Flag enabling the translation of the texts using AWS service. Can take two values: Yes: Translates the texts; No: Do not translate the texts.  The Yes flag can only be used in production mode.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;CATALOGUE_READER_SELECT: Flag enabling the reading of the metadata from the P/T web service. Can take two values: Yes: Read the metadata from the P/T web service; No: Read the metadata from a local source on disk.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;FORCED_PYCSW_URL: URL address of the PYCSW server used to update the metadata.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_FFS_TESTING_FILE: Name of a FFS file containing the metadata records read from the CATALOGUE_READER. This file is used when the parameter: &lt;em&gt;CATALOGUE_READER_SELECT&lt;/em&gt; is set to &lt;em&gt;No&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LOCAL_SOURCE_METADATA_DELTA_FINDER: Flag enabling the use of a local source for the metadata delta finder. Can take two values: Yes: Use a local source as defined by the parameter OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR; No: use the content PyCSW server as defined by the parameter: FORCED_PYCSW_URL.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LOCAL_WRITER: Flag enabling to write the output locally or on the server.  Can take two values: Yes: Write the output locally as defined by the parameter:OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR; No: Write the output in the PyCSW server as defined by the parameter: FORCEDS_PYCSW_URL.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;P_T_ABBR: Two letter abbreviation code of the province or terrirtory (ex.: ON, QC, ...).&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;METADATA_OVERWRITE: Enable the overwite of the PyCSW.  Can take two values: Yes: Overwrite the contentof the PyCSW; No: Do no overwrite the content of the PyCSW.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_OUT_WORKING_DIR: Root working directory used to define the following &lt;em&gt;private parameters&lt;/em&gt;:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;IN_CSV_LOOKUP_TABLES_DIR: Source directory of the root of the lookup table files. Defined as: \\LOOKUP_TABLES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;IN_GMD_XML_TEMPLATES_DIR: Source directory of the root XML templates. Defined as: \\XML_TEMPLATES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;INJSON_TEMPLATE_DIR: Source directory of the root JSON templates. Defined as: \\JSON_TEMPLATES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;LOG_FILE: Output log file. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\LOG\\QC.log&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_JSON_LOCAL_DIR: Source directory to output JSON files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\JSON_LOCAL&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XLS_NOTIFICATION: Source directory to output excel files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XLS&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_FAILED_DIR: Source directory to output failed XML files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XML_FAILED&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR: Source directory to output &lt;em&gt;Local Source&lt;/em&gt; XML files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XML_LOCAL&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_PASSED_DIR: Source directory to output passedXML files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XML_PASSED&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;SAMPLE_SIZE: Number of features to process. Zero (0) means process all the features. A number &lt;em&gt;n&lt;/em&gt; greater than 0 means sample or process only the first &lt;em&gt;n&lt;/em&gt; features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;URL_VALIDATION : Indicates to validate or not created URL. (Should be Yes for prod)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-20T15:48:37-05:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:51:43-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;Mac_Valley_PROD.fmw&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;NL_FGP_BUILDER_PRO&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalRuns&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;WORKSPACE&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;steven-poulin&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This custom transformer sets manually the spatial representation type.  The supplied lookup table contains the ID and the spatial representation type for a subset of the metadata records.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;LOOKUP_TABLE_INPUT: Input information from the lookup table&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;DATA_INPUT: The input metadata records to process.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;GEOSPATIAL: Output port for the geospatial metadata records&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;NON-GEOSPATIAL: Output port for the non geospatial metadata records&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;UNMAPPED_DATA: Output port for the metadata records for which the spatial representation type cannot be determine.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;FEATURE_TYPE: Name of the CSV file to read (without .csv extension);&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_CSV_LOOKUP_TABLES_DIR: Name of the directory path containing the CSV file to read;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;P-T_ABBR: Two letters abbreviation of the province or the territory.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:22-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T12:40:29-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;MANUAL_GEOSPATIAL_SETTER_NG.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;MANUAL_GEOSPATIAL_SETTER_NG&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This transformer tests if the ressources{}.url from the metadata records are present in the lookup table, if yes then it sets the xlink_role and protocol attributes&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;INPUT: Input metadata records to process.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUTPUT: The process output metdata records.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;FEATURE_TYPE: Name of the CSV file to read (without .csv extension);&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_CSV_LOOKUP_TABLES_DIR: Name of the directory path containing the CSV file to read;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;P-T_ABBR: Two letters abbreviation of the province or the territory.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:23-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T12:40:51-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;MAP_RESOURCE_ATTRIBUTION_REMOVER_NG.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;MAP_RESOURCE_ATTRIBUTION_REMOVER_NG&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuPct&quot;: 55.837040388046944, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuTime&quot;: 155519, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgElapsedTime&quot;: 278523, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgPeakMemUsage&quot;: 830382295, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This workbench read and trasform all the metadata for the provinces of Manitoba (MB) and Saskatchewan (SK).&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;None&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;None&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_GEO: Flag enabling the processing of the geospatial features. Can take two values: Yes: Process the geospatial features; No: Do not process the geospatial features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_NON_GEO: Flag enabling the processing of the none geospatial features. Can take two values: Yes: Process the none geospatial features; No: Do not process the none geospatial features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_TRANSLATION: Flag enabling the translation of the texts using AWS service. Can take two values: Yes: Translates the texts; No: Do not translate the texts.  The Yes flag can only be used in production mode.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;DCAT_READER_SELECT: Flag enabling the reading of the metadata from the P/T web service. Can take two values: Yes: Read the metadata from the P/T web service; No: Read the metadata from a local source on disk.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;FORCED_PYCSW_URL: URL address of the PYCSW server used to update the metadata.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_FFS_TESTING_FILE: Name of a FFS file containing the metadata records read from the DCAT_READER. This file is used when the parameter: &lt;em&gt;DCAT_READER_SELECT&lt;/em&gt; is set to &lt;em&gt;No&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LOCAL_SOURCE_METADATA_DELTA_FINDER: Flag enabling the use of a local source for the metadata delta finder. Can take two values: Yes: Use a local source as defined by the parameter OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR; No: use the content PyCSW server as defined by the parameter: FORCED_PYCSW_URL.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LOCAL_WRITER: Flag enabling to write the output locally or on the server.  Can take two values: Yes: Write the output locally as defined by the parameter:OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR; No: Write the output in the PyCSW server as defined by the parameter: FORCEDS_PYCSW_URL.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;P-T_ABBR: SK or MB&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;METADATA_OVERWRITE: Enable the overwite of the PyCSW.  Can take two values: Yes: Overwrite the contentof the PyCSW; No: Do no overwrite the content of the PyCSW.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_OUT_WORKING_DIR: Root working directory used to define the following &lt;em&gt;private parameters&lt;/em&gt;:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;IN_CSV_LOOKUP_TABLES_DIR: Source directory of the root of the lookup table files. Defined as: \\LOOKUP_TABLES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;IN_GMD_XML_TEMPLATES_DIR: Source directory of the root XML templates. Defined as: \\XML_TEMPLATES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;INJSON_TEMPLATE_DIR: Source directory of the root JSON templates. Defined as: \\JSON_TEMPLATES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;LOG_FILE: Output log file. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\LOG\\QC.log&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_JSON_LOCAL_DIR: Source directory to output JSON files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\JSON_LOCAL&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XLS_NOTIFICATION: Source directory to output excel files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XLS&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_FAILED_DIR: Source directory to output failed XML files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XML_FAILED&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR: Source directory to output &lt;em&gt;Local Source&lt;/em&gt; XML files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XML_LOCAL&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_PASSED_DIR: Source directory to output passedXML files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XML_PASSED&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;URL_VALIDATION : Indicates to validate or not created URL. (Should be Yes for prod)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;VALIDATE_INSERT_PCT :Indicates to valide insert percentage. 75 % or less insert/update record  (Should be Yes for prod)&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-20T15:48:39-05:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:52:05-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;MB_SK_PROD.fmw&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;MB_SK_PROD&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalRuns&quot;: 19, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;WORKSPACE&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;steven-poulin&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuPct&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuTime&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgElapsedTime&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgPeakMemUsage&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This workbench read and trasform all the metadata for the provinces of Manitoba (MB) and Saskatchewan (SK).&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;None&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;None&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_GEO: Flag enabling the processing of the geospatial features. Can take two values: Yes: Process the geospatial features; No: Do not process the geospatial features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_NON_GEO: Flag enabling the processing of the none geospatial features. Can take two values: Yes: Process the none geospatial features; No: Do not process the none geospatial features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_TRANSLATION: Flag enabling the translation of the texts using AWS service. Can take two values: Yes: Translates the texts; No: Do not translate the texts.  The Yes flag can only be used in production mode.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;DCAT_READER_SELECT: Flag enabling the reading of the metadata from the P/T web service. Can take two values: Yes: Read the metadata from the P/T web service; No: Read the metadata from a local source on disk.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;FORCED_PYCSW_URL: URL address of the PYCSW server used to update the metadata.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_FFS_TESTING_FILE: Name of a FFS file containing the metadata records read from the DCAT_READER. This file is used when the parameter: &lt;em&gt;DCAT_READER_SELECT&lt;/em&gt; is set to &lt;em&gt;No&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LOCAL_SOURCE_METADATA_DELTA_FINDER: Flag enabling the use of a local source for the metadata delta finder. Can take two values: Yes: Use a local source as defined by the parameter OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR; No: use the content PyCSW server as defined by the parameter: FORCED_PYCSW_URL.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LOCAL_WRITER: Flag enabling to write the output locally or on the server.  Can take two values: Yes: Write the output locally as defined by the parameter:OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR; No: Write the output in the PyCSW server as defined by the parameter: FORCEDS_PYCSW_URL.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;P-T_ABBR: Two or three letter abbreviation code of the province or terrirtory (ex.: ON, QC, PEI, ...).&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;METADATA_OVERWRITE: Enable the overwite of the PyCSW.  Can take two values: Yes: Overwrite the contentof the PyCSW; No: Do no overwrite the content of the PyCSW.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_OUT_WORKING_DIR: Root working directory defined by default as: &lt;em&gt;(FME_SHAREDRESOURCE_DATA)&lt;/em&gt;\\ &lt;em&gt;PT_Harvester&lt;/em&gt;.  Used to define the following &lt;em&gt;private parameters&lt;/em&gt;:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_CSV_LOOKUP_TABLES_DIR: Source directory of the root of the lookup table files. Defined as: (IN_OUT_WORKING_DIR)\\ &lt;em&gt;LOOKUP_TABLES&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_GMD_XML_TEMPLATE_DIR: Source directory of the root XML templates. Defined as: (IN_OUT_WORKING_DIR)\\ &lt;em&gt;XML_TEMPLATES&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_TBS_JSON_TEMPLATE_DIR: Source directory of the root JSON templates. Defined as: (IN_OUT_WORKING_DIR)\\ &lt;em&gt;JSON_TEMPLATES&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LOG_FILE: Output log file. Defined as: (IN_OUT_WORKING_DIR)\\ (P-T_ABBR)\\ &lt;em&gt;LOG&lt;/em&gt;\\ (P-T_ABBR)&lt;em&gt;.log&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;OUT_JSON_LOCAL_DIR: Source directory to output JSON files. Defined as: (IN_OUT_WORKING_DIR)\\ (P-T_ABBR)\\ &lt;em&gt;JSON_LOCAL&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;OUT_XLS_NOTIFICATION_DIR: Source directory to output excel files. Defined as: (IN_OUT_WORKING_DIR)\\ (P-T_ABBR)\\ &lt;em&gt;XLS&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;OUT_XML_FAILED_DIR: Source directory to output failed XML files. Defined as: (IN_OUT_WORKING_DIR)\\ (P-T_ABBR)\\ &lt;em&gt;XML_FAILED&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR: Source directory to output &lt;em&gt;Local Source&lt;/em&gt; XML files. Defined as: (IN_OUT_WORKING_DIR)\\ (P-T_ABBR)\\ &lt;em&gt;XML_LOCAL&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;OUT_XML_PASSED_DIR: Source directory to output passedXML files. Defined as: (IN_OUT_WORKING_DIR)\\ (P-T_ABBR)\\ &lt;em&gt;XML_PASSED&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;URL_VALIDATION : Indicates to validate or not created URL. (Should be Yes for prod)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-20T15:48:42-05:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:52:36-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;MB_SK_PROD_LangDetection.fmw&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;MB_SK_DEV&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalRuns&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;WORKSPACE&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;steven-poulin&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This custom transformer identify the type of transaction (insert, update, delete, no change) for each metadata records read from the province.  In order to determine the type of transaction, the metadata reference records (from the PYCSW or from a Local Source) are read and are compared using a hash function (see note) with the records from the province (new records). There are four possible types of transaction:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;Insert: A record read from the province is not found in the reference records (PYCSW or Local Source)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;Update: A record read from the province is found in the reference records (PYCSW or Local Source) but with one or more differences in the content of the metadata record&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;Delete: A record is present in the reference record (PYCSW or Local Source) but not in the province&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;No change: A record read from the province is identical (all fields are the same) to a record found in the reference records (PYCSW or Local Source).&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Input: The input metadata records from the province.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;Statistics: The number of unchanged features to pass to the &lt;em&gt;Logger Parameters&lt;/em&gt; transformers;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;No Change: Features that were not modified in regards with the content of the referenced records (PYCSW or Local Source);&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;Update: Features that were updated (modified feature) in regards with the content of the referenced records (PYCSW or Local Source);&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;Insert: Features to insert (new feature) in regards to the content of the referenced records (PYCSW or Local Source);&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;Delete: Features to delete (feature removed) in regards to the content of the referenced records (PYCSW or Local Source).&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;Note: If the parameter &lt;em&gt;METADATA_OVERWRITE&lt;/em&gt; is set to &lt;em&gt;YES&lt;/em&gt;, all the unchanged features are flag as Insert.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;ABSTRACT_ATT_NEW: Name of the attribute containing the description of the abstract for the new record from the province&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ABSTRACT_ATT_REF: Name of the attribute containing the description of the abstract for the reference record (PYCSW or Local source)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;DATESTAMP_ATT_NEW: Name of the attribute containing the date stamp for the new record from the province&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;DATESTAMP_ATT_REF: Name of the attribute containing the date stamp for the reference record (PYCSW or Local source)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ID_ATT_NEW: Name of the attribute containing the identification for the new record from the province&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ID_ATT_REF: Name of the attribute containing the identification for the reference record (PYCSW or Local Source)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;RES_NAME_ATT_NEW: Name of the attribute containing the resource name for the new record from the province&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;RES_NAME_ATT_REF: Name of the attribute containing the resource name for the reference record (PYCSW or Local Source)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;RES_URL_ATT_NEW: Name of the attribute containing the resource URL for the new record from the province&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;RES_URL_ATT_REF: Name of the attribute containing the resource URL for the reference record (PYCSW or Local Source)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;TITLE_ATT_NEW: Name of the attribute containing the title for the new record from the province&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;TITLE_ATT_REF: Name of the attribute containing the title for the reference record (PYCSW or Local Source)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;CUSTOM_CSW_CKAN_URL: Name of the attribute containing the URL of the PYCSW server&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;CKAN_FILTER: Name of the attribute used to filter CKAN records in the PyCSW server&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LOCAL_SOURCE: Flag indicating if the metadata record for identifying the action (insert, update, delete, no change) must be read from the PYCSW server or are stored on the local system. Can take 2 values: YES: read the records from the PYCSW; NO read the records from the Local source.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LOCAL_SOURCE_FORMAT: Flag indicating the type of metadata format format to process.  Can take 2 values: XML to process XML format records (geospatial data); JSON to process JSON format records (non geospatial data)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LOCAL_SOURCE_DIR: Name of the directory containing the local source of the referenced records. Used if LOCAL_SOURCE parameters is set to NO&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;CSW_FILTER: Name of the attribute used to filter CSW records in the PyCSW server in order to select records from one province only&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;RES_FORMAT_ATT_NEW: Name of the attribute containing the format of the resource for the new record from the province&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;RES_FORMAT_ATT_REF: Name of the attribute containing the format of the resource for the reference record (PYCSW or Local Source)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;METADATA_OVERWRITE: Flag indicating to overwrite or not the metadata. Can take 2 values: &lt;em&gt;YES&lt;/em&gt;: Overwrite the content of the PyCSW server; &lt;em&gt;NO&lt;/em&gt;: Do not overwrite the content of the PyCSW server; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Note:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;A hash function using strategic attributes is used to determine if 2 metadata records (features) are the same.&lt;/p&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:23-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T12:45:23-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;METADATA_DELTA_FINDER_GEN.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;METADATA_DELTA_FINDER_GEN&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This custom transformer updates (map) data format values to valid data format values and associate the French and English &apos;Resource Type&apos; attribute to each data format type. It accesses a lookup table to fetch the correct values.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;In order to map the data formats of the feature resources{} attribute list, this custom transformer uses a three steps process. The first step maps the data format according to the values contained in the CSV file.  The second step identify the features that were not correctly map and tries to guess the data format according to the url content and/or structure. The third step maps the data format according to the values contained in the CSV file for the features not correctly map in the second pass.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;DATA_INPUT: The metadata record to process&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;OUTPUT: The output metadata records&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ATT_TO_MAP: Name of the attribute to map in plain text (ex.: resources{}.format).  Do not use the Open Text Editor &amp;gt; FME Feature Attribute option to select the attribute to map;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ERROR_NOT_MAPPED: Flag use to map data items values that cannot be found in the loopup tables. Can take 2 values: Yes: map data values not found; No: Do not map data values not found;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;REAL_VALUE_REFRESH: Flag use for updating data format attribute values. Can take two value: Yes: update data format; No do not update data format;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;RES_TYPE_FR_REFRESH: Flag use for updating French resources type. Can take two value: Yes: update French resource type; No do not update French resource type;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;RES_TYPE_EN_REFRESH: Flag use for updating English resources type. Can take two value: Yes: update English resource type; No do not update English resource type;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;FEATURE_TYPE: Name of the CSV file to read (without .csv extension);&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_CSV_LOOKUP_TABLES_DIR: Name of the directory path containing the CSV file to read;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;P-T_ABBR: Two letters abbreviation of the province or the territory.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:23-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T12:46:42-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;METADATA_FORMAT_MAPPER_NG.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;METADATA_FORMAT_MAPPER_NG&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This transformer tests the more_info{}.link list for non empty value values and filters them out where missing.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;INPUT: Input metadata records to process.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;OUTPUT: The process output metdata records.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;NONE&lt;/p&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:25-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T12:49:50-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;MORE_INFO_MANAGER.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;MORE_INFO_MANAGER&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:25-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T12:59:33-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;NB_FrenchEnglishAttributeSeparator_NG.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;NB_FrenchEnglishAttributeSeparator_NG&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuPct&quot;: 57.82792577288559, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuTime&quot;: 184452, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgElapsedTime&quot;: 318967, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgPeakMemUsage&quot;: 611331276, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This workbench read and trasform all the metadata for the province of New Brunswick (NB)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;None&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;None&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_GEO: Flag enabling the processing of the geospatial features. Can take two values: Yes: Process the geospatial features; No: Do not process the geospatial features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_NON_GEO: Flag enabling the processing of the none geospatial features. Can take two values: Yes: Process the none geospatial features; No: Do not process the none geospatial features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_TRANSLATION: Flag enabling the translation of the texts using AWS service. Can take two values: Yes: Translates the texts; No: Do not translate the texts.  The Yes flag can only be used in production mode.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;CATALOGUE_READER_SELECT: Flag enabling the reading of the metadata from the P/T web service. Can take two values: Yes: Read the metadata from the P/T web service; No: Read the metadata from a local source on disk.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;FORCED_PYCSW_URL: URL address of the PYCSW server used to update the metadata.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_FFS_TESTING_FILE: Name of a FFS file containing the metadata records read from the CATALOGUE_READER. This file is used when the parameter: &lt;em&gt;CATALOGUE_READER_SELECT&lt;/em&gt; is set to &lt;em&gt;No&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LOCAL_SOURCE_METADATA_DELTA_FINDER: Flag enabling the use of a local source for the metadata delta finder. Can take two values: Yes: Use a local source as defined by the parameter OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR; No: use the content PyCSW server as defined by the parameter: FORCED_PYCSW_URL.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LOCAL_WRITER: Flag enabling to write the output locally or on the server.  Can take two values: Yes: Write the output locally as defined by the parameter:OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR; No: Write the output in the PyCSW server as defined by the parameter: FORCEDS_PYCSW_URL.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;METADATA_OVERWRITE: Enable the overwite of the PyCSW.  Can take two values: Yes: Overwrite the contentof the PyCSW; No: Do no overwrite the content of the PyCSW.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_OUT_WORKING_DIR: Root working directory used to define the following &lt;em&gt;private parameters&lt;/em&gt;:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;IN_CSV_LOOKUP_TABLES_DIR: Source directory of the root of the lookup table files. Defined as: \\LOOKUP_TABLES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;IN_GMD_XML_TEMPLATES_DIR: Source directory of the root XML templates. Defined as: \\XML_TEMPLATES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;INJSON_TEMPLATE_DIR: Source directory of the root JSON templates. Defined as: \\JSON_TEMPLATES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;LOG_FILE: Output log file. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\LOG\\QC.log&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_JSON_LOCAL_DIR: Source directory to output JSON files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\JSON_LOCAL&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XLS_NOTIFICATION: Source directory to output excel files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XLS&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_FAILED_DIR: Source directory to output failed XML files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XML_FAILED&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR: Source directory to output &lt;em&gt;Local Source&lt;/em&gt; XML files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XML_LOCAL&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_PASSED_DIR: Source directory to output passedXML files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XML_PASSED&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;SAMPLE_SIZE: Number of features to process. Zero (0) means process all the features. A number &lt;em&gt;n&lt;/em&gt; greater than 0 means sample or process only the first &lt;em&gt;n&lt;/em&gt; features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;URL_VALIDATION : Indicates to validate or not created URL. (Should be Yes for prod)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;VALIDATE_INSERT_PCT :Indicates to valide insert percentage. 75 % or less insert/update record  (Should be Yes for prod)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-11T16:00:08-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-11T16:00:07-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;NB_PROD.fmw&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;NB_PROD&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalRuns&quot;: 5, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;WORKSPACE&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This custom transformer extracts from the flatten XML (XHTML), the tags of the metadata information and transformed them into FME attributes. The XHTML tags information are renamed with the appropriate name to facilitate the following processes.  The custom transformer deletes the flatten XML attributes.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Note: This custom transformer will not produce the same result if the HTML tags are modified by the owner of the web site even for a small change in the layout of the information.  Some XHTML tags are not optional so it&apos;s impossible to distinguish a missing tag from a tag that was renamed.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;The flatten XHTML code.  On feature per dataset.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;The fatures with extracted information in FME attributes.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:25-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T12:59:50-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;NL_ATTRIBUTE_EXTRACTOR.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;NL_ATTRIBUTE_EXTRACTOR&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This Custom Transformer is used to read the metadata of the NewFoundLand &amp;amp; Labrador open data portal.  The portal is not offering a public APi to access the metdata information so, this custom transformer is reading all the XHTML code and flatten it in order to parse it and extract the needed metadata information.  The metadata extraction is done is two passes. The first passes to extrat the name and the url of each dataset.  A second pass is done to read the complete set of  metadata of each url (one url per dataset).&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Note: There is no option to read only one record with a specific identifier.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Input: One feature to start the extraction of all the records from the NewFoundLand &amp;amp; Labrador open data portal.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Résultats: All the records read from the NewFoundLand &amp;amp; Labrador open data portal&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;URL_ROOT: URL of the  NewFoundLand &amp;amp; Labrador open data portal.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;URL_DATASET_GEO: URL prefix of the metadata of the geospatial datasets.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;URL_DATASET_NON_GEO: URL prefix of the metadata of the non geospatial datasets.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:25-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:02:03-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;NL_CATALOGUE_READER.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;NL_CATALOGUE_READER&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuPct&quot;: 29.38890558451383, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuTime&quot;: 28360, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgElapsedTime&quot;: 96499, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgPeakMemUsage&quot;: 457782737, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This workbench read and trasform all the metadata for the province of NewFoundLand &amp;amp; Labrador (NL)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;None&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;None&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_GEO: Flag enabling the processing of the geospatial features. Can take two values: Yes: Process the geospatial features; No: Do not process the geospatial features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_NON_GEO: Flag enabling the processing of the none geospatial features. Can take two values: Yes: Process the none geospatial features; No: Do not process the none geospatial features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_TRANSLATION: Flag enabling the translation of the texts using AWS service. Can take two values: Yes: Translates the texts; No: Do not translate the texts.  The Yes flag can only be used in production mode.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;CATALOGUE_READER_SELECT: Flag enabling the reading of the metadata from the P/T web service. Can take two values: Yes: Read the metadata from the P/T web service; No: Read the metadata from a local source on disk.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;FORCED_PYCSW_URL: URL address of the PYCSW server used to update the metadata.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_FFS_TESTING_FILE: Name of a FFS file containing the metadata records read from the CATALOGUE_READER. This file is used when the parameter: &lt;em&gt;CATALOGUE_READER_SELECT&lt;/em&gt; is set to &lt;em&gt;No&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LOCAL_SOURCE_METADATA_DELTA_FINDER: Flag enabling the use of a local source for the metadata delta finder. Can take two values: Yes: Use a local source as defined by the parameter OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR; No: use the content PyCSW server as defined by the parameter: FORCED_PYCSW_URL.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LOCAL_WRITER: Flag enabling to write the output locally or on the server.  Can take two values: Yes: Write the output locally as defined by the parameter:OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR; No: Write the output in the PyCSW server as defined by the parameter: FORCEDS_PYCSW_URL.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;P_T_ABBR: Two letter abbreviation code of the province or terrirtory (ex.: ON, QC, ...).&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;METADATA_OVERWRITE: Enable the overwite of the PyCSW.  Can take two values: Yes: Overwrite the contentof the PyCSW; No: Do no overwrite the content of the PyCSW.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_OUT_WORKING_DIR: Root working directory used to define the following &lt;em&gt;private parameters&lt;/em&gt;:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;IN_CSV_LOOKUP_TABLES_DIR: Source directory of the root of the lookup table files. Defined as: \\LOOKUP_TABLES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;IN_GMD_XML_TEMPLATES_DIR: Source directory of the root XML templates. Defined as: \\XML_TEMPLATES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;INJSON_TEMPLATE_DIR: Source directory of the root JSON templates. Defined as: \\JSON_TEMPLATES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;LOG_FILE: Output log file. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\LOG\\QC.log&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_JSON_LOCAL_DIR: Source directory to output JSON files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\JSON_LOCAL&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XLS_NOTIFICATION: Source directory to output excel files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XLS&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_FAILED_DIR: Source directory to output failed XML files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XML_FAILED&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR: Source directory to output &lt;em&gt;Local Source&lt;/em&gt; XML files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XML_LOCAL&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_PASSED_DIR: Source directory to output passedXML files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XML_PASSED&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;SAMPLE_SIZE: Number of features to process. Zero (0) means process all the features. A number &lt;em&gt;n&lt;/em&gt; greater than 0 means sample or process only the first &lt;em&gt;n&lt;/em&gt; features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;URL_VALIDATION : Indicates to validate or not created URL. (Should be Yes for prod)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;VALIDATE_INSERT_PCT :Indicates to valide insert percentage. 75 % or less insert/update record  (Should be Yes for prod)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-20T15:48:39-05:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:53:21-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;NL_PROD.fmw&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;NL_PROD&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalRuns&quot;: 11, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;WORKSPACE&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;steven-poulin&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuPct&quot;: 69.06571040304794, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuTime&quot;: 450296, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgElapsedTime&quot;: 651982, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgPeakMemUsage&quot;: 848840021, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This workbench read and trasform all the metadata for the province of Nova-Scotia (NS)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;None&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;None&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_GEO: Flag enabling the processing of the geospatial features. Can take two values: Yes: Process the geospatial features; No: Do not process the geospatial features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_NON_GEO: Flag enabling the processing of the none geospatial features. Can take two values: Yes: Process the none geospatial features; No: Do not process the none geospatial features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_TRANSLATION: Flag enabling the translation of the texts using AWS service. Can take two values: Yes: Translates the texts; No: Do not translate the texts.  The Yes flag can only be used in production mode.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;CATALOGUE_READER_SELECT: Flag enabling the reading of the metadata from the P/T web service. Can take two values: Yes: Read the metadata from the P/T web service; No: Read the metadata from a local source on disk.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;FORCED_PYCSW_URL: URL address of the PYCSW server used to update the metadata.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_FFS_TESTING_FILE: Name of a FFS file containing the metadata records read from the CATALOGUE_READER. This file is used when the parameter: &lt;em&gt;CATALOGUE_READER_SELECT&lt;/em&gt; is set to &lt;em&gt;No&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LOCAL_SOURCE_METADATA_DELTA_FINDER: Flag enabling the use of a local source for the metadata delta finder. Can take two values: Yes: Use a local source as defined by the parameter OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR; No: use the content PyCSW server as defined by the parameter: FORCED_PYCSW_URL.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LOCAL_WRITER: Flag enabling to write the output locally or on the server.  Can take two values: Yes: Write the output locally as defined by the parameter:OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR; No: Write the output in the PyCSW server as defined by the parameter: FORCEDS_PYCSW_URL.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;METADATA_OVERWRITE: Enable the overwite of the PyCSW.  Can take two values: Yes: Overwrite the contentof the PyCSW; No: Do no overwrite the content of the PyCSW.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_OUT_WORKING_DIR: Root working directory used to define the following &lt;em&gt;private parameters&lt;/em&gt;:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;IN_CSV_LOOKUP_TABLES_DIR: Source directory of the root of the lookup table files. Defined as: \\LOOKUP_TABLES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;IN_GMD_XML_TEMPLATES_DIR: Source directory of the root XML templates. Defined as: \\XML_TEMPLATES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;INJSON_TEMPLATE_DIR: Source directory of the root JSON templates. Defined as: \\JSON_TEMPLATES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;LOG_FILE: Output log file. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\LOG\\QC.log&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_JSON_LOCAL_DIR: Source directory to output JSON files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\JSON_LOCAL&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XLS_NOTIFICATION: Source directory to output excel files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XLS&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_FAILED_DIR: Source directory to output failed XML files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XML_FAILED&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR: Source directory to output &lt;em&gt;Local Source&lt;/em&gt; XML files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XML_LOCAL&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_PASSED_DIR: Source directory to output passedXML files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XML_PASSED&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;SAMPLE_SIZE: Number of features to process. Zero (0) means process all the features. A number &lt;em&gt;n&lt;/em&gt; greater than 0 means sample or process only the first &lt;em&gt;n&lt;/em&gt; features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;URL_VALIDATION : Indicates to validate or not created URL. (Should be Yes for prod)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;VALIDATE_INSERT_PCT :Indicates to valide insert percentage. 75 % or less insert/update record  (Should be Yes for prod)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-12T10:11:26-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-12T10:11:25-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;NS_PROD.fmw&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;NS_PROD&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalRuns&quot;: 6, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;WORKSPACE&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This Custom Transformer is used to read the metadata of the North West Territories open data portal (https://www.geomatics.gov.nt.ca/en/resources).  The portal is not offering a public API to access the metdata information so, this custom transformer is reading all the XHTML code and flatten it in order to parse it and extract the needed metadata information.  &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Note: There is no option to read only one record with a specific identifier.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Input: One feature to start the extraction of all the records from the North West Territories open data portal.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;DATA: All the metadata records from the DATA catalog&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;MAPS: All the metadata records from the MAPS catalog&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;WMS: All the metadata records from the WMS catalog&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;REPORTS: All the metadata records from the REPORTS catalog&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;DOCUMENTS: All the metadata records from the DOCUMENTS catalog&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;MAPS_VIEWERS: All the metadata records from the MAPS_VIWERS catalog&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;DATA_METADATA: Flag to enable or disable reading the DATA catalog (default: Yes).&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;MAPS_METADATA: Flag to enable or disable reading the MAPS catalog (default: Yes).&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;WMS_METADATA: Flag to enable or disable reading the WMS catalog (default: Yes).&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;REPORTS_METADATA: Flag to enable or disable reading the REPORTS catalog (default: Yes).&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;DOCUMENTS_METADATA: Flag to enable or disable reading the DOCUMENTS catalog (default: Yes).&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;MAPS_VIEWERS_METADATA: Flag to enable or disable reading the MAPS_VIEWERS catalog (default: Yes).&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:26-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:02:21-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;NT_CATALOGUE_READER.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;NT_CATALOGUE_READER&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;This custom transformer uses a look-up table with the url of each resources where the list attribute language{} contains the value &apos;fr&apos; and change the value of resources{}.language to &apos;en-fr&apos; for Alberta province in the P/T project of the FGP.&lt;/p&gt; &quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:26-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:02:37-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;NT_language_manager.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;NT_language_manager&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:26-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:03:53-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;NT_metadata_merger.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;NT_metadata_merger&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuPct&quot;: 41.396347154473865, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuTime&quot;: 145035, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgElapsedTime&quot;: 350357, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgPeakMemUsage&quot;: 501143552, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This workbench read and trasform all the metadata for the Northwest Territory (NT)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;None&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;None&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_GEO: Flag enabling the processing of the geospatial features. Can take two values: Yes: Process the geospatial features; No: Do not process the geospatial features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_NON_GEO: Flag enabling the processing of the none geospatial features. Can take two values: Yes: Process the none geospatial features; No: Do not process the none geospatial features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_TRANSLATION: Flag enabling the translation of the texts using AWS service. Can take two values: Yes: Translates the texts; No: Do not translate the texts.  The Yes flag can only be used in production mode.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;CATALOGUE_READER_SELECT: Flag enabling the reading of the metadata from the P/T web service. Can take two values: Yes: Read the metadata from the P/T web service; No: Read the metadata from a local source on disk.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;FORCED_PYCSW_URL: URL address of the PYCSW server used to update the metadata.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_FFS_TESTING_FILE: Name of a FFS file containing the metadata records read from the CATALOGUE_READER. This file is used when the parameter: &lt;em&gt;CATALOGUE_READER_SELECT&lt;/em&gt; is set to &lt;em&gt;No&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LOCAL_SOURCE_METADATA_DELTA_FINDER: Flag enabling the use of a local source for the metadata delta finder. Can take two values: Yes: Use a local source as defined by the parameter OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR; No: use the content PyCSW server as defined by the parameter: FORCED_PYCSW_URL.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LOCAL_WRITER: Flag enabling to write the output locally or on the server.  Can take two values: Yes: Write the output locally as defined by the parameter:OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR; No: Write the output in the PyCSW server as defined by the parameter: FORCEDS_PYCSW_URL.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;METADATA_OVERWRITE: Enable the overwite of the PyCSW.  Can take two values: Yes: Overwrite the contentof the PyCSW; No: Do no overwrite the content of the PyCSW.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_OUT_WORKING_DIR: Root working directory used to define the following &lt;em&gt;private parameters&lt;/em&gt;:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;IN_CSV_LOOKUP_TABLES_DIR: Source directory of the root of the lookup table files. Defined as: \\LOOKUP_TABLES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;IN_GMD_XML_TEMPLATES_DIR: Source directory of the root XML templates. Defined as: \\XML_TEMPLATES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;INJSON_TEMPLATE_DIR: Source directory of the root JSON templates. Defined as: \\JSON_TEMPLATES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;LOG_FILE: Output log file. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\LOG\\QC.log&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_JSON_LOCAL_DIR: Source directory to output JSON files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\JSON_LOCAL&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XLS_NOTIFICATION: Source directory to output excel files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XLS&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_FAILED_DIR: Source directory to output failed XML files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XML_FAILED&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR: Source directory to output &lt;em&gt;Local Source&lt;/em&gt; XML files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XML_LOCAL&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_PASSED_DIR: Source directory to output passedXML files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XML_PASSED&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;SAMPLE_SIZE: Number of features to process. Zero (0) means process all the features. A number &lt;em&gt;n&lt;/em&gt; greater than 0 means sample or process only the first &lt;em&gt;n&lt;/em&gt; features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;URL_VALIDATION : Indicates to validate or not created URL. (Should be Yes for prod)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;VALIDATE_INSERT_PCT :Indicates to valide insert percentage. 75 % or less insert/update record  (Should be Yes for prod)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-20T15:48:42-05:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:55:14-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;NT_PROD.fmw&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;NT_PROD&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalRuns&quot;: 6, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;WORKSPACE&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;steven-poulin&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:27-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:04:17-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;NT_resources_merger.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;NT_resources_merger&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Custom transformer désigné pour l&apos;extraction des formulaires de contact pour pour l&apos;ontario. Pour l&apos;Ontario, chaque organisation a sa propre page de formulaire pour permettre aux usagers de les contater&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Dépendance: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ce custom se connecte à l&apos;API CKAN pour extraire org_contact.fr et org_contact.en.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Input: Métadonnées de la province de l&apos;Ontario avec le champ organization.id défini&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Output: Métadonnée sur laquelle on a ajouté org_contact.fr et org_contact.en&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Paramètre&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;CKAN_ROOT: Root de la province. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Erreurs: &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;ERREUR: Impossible d&apos;effectuer la requête à CKAN pour avoir les organisations --&amp;gt; Vérifier l&apos;URL&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;ERREUR: Impossible d&apos;applatir le JSON pour extraire le contenu --&amp;gt; Ne devrait pas arriver&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;ERREUR: Impossible d&apos;exploser la liste result --&amp;gt; Vérifier le modèle de données&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:27-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:05:28-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;ON_CKAN_CONTACT_FORM_EXTRACTOR.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;ON_CKAN_CONTACT_FORM_EXTRACTOR&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:28-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:05:58-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;ON_DATE_FORMATTER.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;ON_DATE_FORMATTER&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:28-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:08:59-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;ON_GEOHUB_RESOURCE_EXTRACTOR.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;ON_GEOHUB_RESOURCE_EXTRACTOR&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:29-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:09:20-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;ON_KEYWORD_RENAMER.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;ON_KEYWORD_RENAMER&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuPct&quot;: 61.96773490205467, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuTime&quot;: 579785, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgElapsedTime&quot;: 935624, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgPeakMemUsage&quot;: 883896320, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This workbench read and trasform all the metadata for the province of Ontario (ON)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;None&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;None&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_GEO: Flag enabling the processing of the geospatial features. Can take two values: Yes: Process the geospatial features; No: Do not process the geospatial features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_NON_GEO: Flag enabling the processing of the none geospatial features. Can take two values: Yes: Process the none geospatial features; No: Do not process the none geospatial features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_TRANSLATION: Flag enabling the translation of the texts using AWS service. Can take two values: Yes: Translates the texts; No: Do not translate the texts.  The Yes flag can only be used in production mode.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;CATALOGUE_READER_SELECT: Flag enabling the reading of the metadata from the P/T web service. Can take two values: Yes: Read the metadata from the P/T web service; No: Read the metadata from a local source on disk.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;FORCED_PYCSW_URL: URL address of the PYCSW server used to update the metadata.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_FFS_TESTING_FILE: Name of a FFS file containing the metadata records read from the CATALOGUE_READER. This file is used when the parameter: &lt;em&gt;CATALOGUE_READER_SELECT&lt;/em&gt; is set to &lt;em&gt;No&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LOCAL_SOURCE_METADATA_DELTA_FINDER: Flag enabling the use of a local source for the metadata delta finder. Can take two values: Yes: Use a local source as defined by the parameter OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR; No: use the content PyCSW server as defined by the parameter: FORCED_PYCSW_URL.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LOCAL_WRITER: Flag enabling to write the output locally or on the server.  Can take two values: Yes: Write the output locally as defined by the parameter:OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR; No: Write the output in the PyCSW server as defined by the parameter: FORCEDS_PYCSW_URL.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;METADATA_OVERWRITE: Enable the overwite of the PyCSW.  Can take two values: Yes: Overwrite the contentof the PyCSW; No: Do no overwrite the content of the PyCSW.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_OUT_WORKING_DIR: Root working directory used to define the following &lt;em&gt;private parameters&lt;/em&gt;:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;IN_CSV_LOOKUP_TABLES_DIR: Source directory of the root of the lookup table files. Defined as: \\LOOKUP_TABLES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;IN_GMD_XML_TEMPLATES_DIR: Source directory of the root XML templates. Defined as: \\XML_TEMPLATES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;INJSON_TEMPLATE_DIR: Source directory of the root JSON templates. Defined as: \\JSON_TEMPLATES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;LOG_FILE: Output log file. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\LOG\\QC.log&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_JSON_LOCAL_DIR: Source directory to output JSON files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\JSON_LOCAL&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XLS_NOTIFICATION: Source directory to output excel files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XLS&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_FAILED_DIR: Source directory to output failed XML files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XML_FAILED&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR: Source directory to output &lt;em&gt;Local Source&lt;/em&gt; XML files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XML_LOCAL&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_PASSED_DIR: Source directory to output passedXML files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XML_PASSED&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;SAMPLE_SIZE: Number of features to process. Zero (0) means process all the features. A number &lt;em&gt;n&lt;/em&gt; greater than 0 means sample or process only the first &lt;em&gt;n&lt;/em&gt; features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;URL_VALIDATION : Indicates to validate or not created URL. (Should be Yes for prod)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;VALIDATE_INSERT_PCT :Indicates to valide insert percentage. 75 % or less insert/update record  (Should be Yes for prod)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-20T15:48:39-05:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-17T13:03:14-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;ON_PROD.fmw&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;ON_PROD&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalRuns&quot;: 3, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;WORKSPACE&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;steven-poulin&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:29-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:09:46-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;ON_TopicExtractor.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;ON_TopicExtractor&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuPct&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuTime&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgElapsedTime&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgPeakMemUsage&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-weight:600;\&quot;&gt;Description:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;Ce programme génère les fichiers GeoDCat destinés au portail OSDP. Le programme est divisé en 2 partie. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-style:italic;\&quot;&gt;Partie 1: Identifier l&apos;action pour chaque métadonnée&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;La première partie consiste à comparer le contenu des répertoires avec l&apos;historique de transfert OSDP pour déterminer l&apos;action à faire pour chaque identifiant de métadonnées.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9;Logique:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9;   - Identifiant présent dans l&apos;historique et sur le disque --&amp;gt; mode Update &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9;   - Identifiant présent dans les fichiers sur le disque mais absent de l&apos;historique--&amp;gt; mode Update et on ajoute l&apos;identifiant dans l&apos;historique pour la prochaine exécution&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9;  - Identifiant présent dans l&apos;historique mais absent du disque --&amp;gt; Mode Delete &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9;Historique de transfert:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9;  - Table dans une base de données, (Postgres ou SQLLite) contenant la province et l&apos;identifiant &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9;   CREATE TABLE \&quot;bd_reference\&quot; (provider character varying(5) NOT NULL, uuid_pt character varying(100) NOT NULL)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9;  Répertoire du dique:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9;  - Le programme est fait pour travailler selon l&apos;arborescence du projet PT.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9;&#9;  PT_Harverster/Prov/JSON_LOCAL&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-style:italic;\&quot;&gt;Partie 2:Transformation de la métadonnée vers le modèle GeoDCat&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;En deuxièem partie du programme, on traduit les métadonnées vers le modèle GeoDCat en application les diverses transformations tel que définies dans la specification d&apos;OSDP.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-weight:600;\&quot;&gt;Paramètres du programme:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;Provider: Code de la province pour laquelle produire les GeoDCat. ALL--&amp;gt; Toutes les provinces&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;IN_OUT_PG_SCHEMA  Schema BD postgres pour l&apos;historique&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;IN_OUT_PG_HOST   Host de la BD prostgres pour l&apos;historique&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;IN_OUT_PG_PORT  Port de la BD postgres pour l&apos;historique&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;IN_OUT_PG_DBNAME   Nom de la BD postgres pour l&apos;historique&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;IN_OUT_PG_USERNAME  Usager pour la BD postgres pour l&apos;historique&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;IN_OUT_PG_PWD  Mot de passe pour la BD postgres pour l&apos;historique&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;ou&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;IN_OUT_SQLITE   Fichier SQL Lite contenant l&apos;historique&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;LOG_FILE&#9;Log du programme&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;IN_CSV_LOOKUP_TABLES_DIR   Répertoire où se trouve le LUT . Par défaut, la valeur est défini au path de production.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;WORKING_DIR&#9;Répertoire où s&apos;effectue le travail. Par défaut, la valeur est défini au path de production.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-weight:600;\&quot;&gt;Intrants:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;- Historique de transfert vers OSDP &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;- Fichiers JSON contenant des métadonnées en format CKANExt pour la fédération de données&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-weight:600;\&quot;&gt;Extrants:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;- Fichiers GeoDCat, regroupé par province pour les Updates, max 100 par fichier&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;- Fichiers GeoDCat, regroupé par provinice pour les Deletes. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-20T15:48:42-05:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:56:31-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;OSDP_NoneGeo_PROD.fmw&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;OSDP_nonGeo&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalRuns&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;WORKSPACE&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;steven-poulin&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuPct&quot;: 52.9502087729538, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuTime&quot;: 58968, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgElapsedTime&quot;: 111365, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgPeakMemUsage&quot;: 385952426, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This workbench read and trasform all the metadata for the provinces of Manitoba (MB) and Saskatchewan (SK).&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;None&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;None&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_GEO: Flag enabling the processing of the geospatial features. Can take two values: Yes: Process the geospatial features; No: Do not process the geospatial features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_NON_GEO: Flag enabling the processing of the none geospatial features. Can take two values: Yes: Process the none geospatial features; No: Do not process the none geospatial features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_TRANSLATION: Flag enabling the translation of the texts using AWS service. Can take two values: Yes: Translates the texts; No: Do not translate the texts.  The Yes flag can only be used in production mode.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;DCAT_READER_SELECT: Flag enabling the reading of the metadata from the P/T web service. Can take two values: Yes: Read the metadata from the P/T web service; No: Read the metadata from a local source on disk.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;FORCED_PYCSW_URL: URL address of the PYCSW server used to update the metadata.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_FFS_TESTING_FILE: Name of a FFS file containing the metadata records read from the DCAT_READER. This file is used when the parameter: &lt;em&gt;DCAT_READER_SELECT&lt;/em&gt; is set to &lt;em&gt;No&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LOCAL_SOURCE_METADATA_DELTA_FINDER: Flag enabling the use of a local source for the metadata delta finder. Can take two values: Yes: Use a local source as defined by the parameter OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR; No: use the content PyCSW server as defined by the parameter: FORCED_PYCSW_URL.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LOCAL_WRITER: Flag enabling to write the output locally or on the server.  Can take two values: Yes: Write the output locally as defined by the parameter:OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR; No: Write the output in the PyCSW server as defined by the parameter: FORCEDS_PYCSW_URL.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;METADATA_OVERWRITE: Enable the overwite of the PyCSW.  Can take two values: Yes: Overwrite the contentof the PyCSW; No: Do no overwrite the content of the PyCSW.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_OUT_WORKING_DIR: Root working directory used to define the following &lt;em&gt;private parameters&lt;/em&gt;:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;IN_CSV_LOOKUP_TABLES_DIR: Source directory of the root of the lookup table files. Defined as: \\LOOKUP_TABLES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;IN_GMD_XML_TEMPLATES_DIR: Source directory of the root XML templates. Defined as: \\XML_TEMPLATES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;INJSON_TEMPLATE_DIR: Source directory of the root JSON templates. Defined as: \\JSON_TEMPLATES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;LOG_FILE: Output log file. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\LOG\\QC.log&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_JSON_LOCAL_DIR: Source directory to output JSON files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\JSON_LOCAL&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XLS_NOTIFICATION: Source directory to output excel files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XLS&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_FAILED_DIR: Source directory to output failed XML files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XML_FAILED&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR: Source directory to output &lt;em&gt;Local Source&lt;/em&gt; XML files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XML_LOCAL&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_PASSED_DIR: Source directory to output passedXML files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XML_PASSED&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;URL_VALIDATION : Indicates to validate or not created URL. (Should be Yes for prod)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;VALIDATE_INSERT_PCT :Indicates to valide insert percentage. 75 % or less insert/update record  (Should be Yes for prod)&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-20T15:48:39-05:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:57:00-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;PEI_PROD.fmw&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;PEI_PROD&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalRuns&quot;: 3, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;WORKSPACE&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;steven-poulin&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:29-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:10:07-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;PEI_TopicExtractor.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;PEI_TopicExtractor&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Add the attribute &lt;em&gt;default contact email&lt;/em&gt; when the attribute &lt;em&gt;contacts{0}.mail&lt;/em&gt; is empty&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;DATA_INPUT: The input metadata records to process.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUTPUT: The process output metdata records.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;-&lt;em&gt; None&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:29-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:10:24-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;QC_MISSING_EMAIL_SETTER.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;QC_MISSING_EMAIL_SETTER&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuPct&quot;: 85.7247868929992, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuTime&quot;: 768521, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgElapsedTime&quot;: 896498, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgPeakMemUsage&quot;: 964992204, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This workbench read and trasform all the metadata for the province of Québec (QC)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;None&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;None&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_GEO: Flag enabling the processing of the geospatial features. Can take two values: Yes: Process the geospatial features; No: Do not process the geospatial features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_NON_GEO: Flag enabling the processing of the none geospatial features. Can take two values: Yes: Process the none geospatial features; No: Do not process the none geospatial features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ACTIVATE_TRANSLATION: Flag enabling the translation of the texts using AWS service. Can take two values: Yes: Translates the texts; No: Do not translate the texts.  The Yes flag can only be used in production mode.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;CATALOGUE_READER_SELECT: Flag enabling the reading of the metadata from the P/T web service. Can take two values: Yes: Read the metadata from the P/T web service; No: Read the metadata from a local source on disk.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;FORCED_PYCSW_URL: URL address of the PYCSW server used to update the metadata.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_FFS_TESTING_FILE: Name of a FFS file containing the metadata records read from the CATALOGUE_READER. This file is used when the parameter: &lt;em&gt;CATALOGUE_READER_SELECT&lt;/em&gt; is set to &lt;em&gt;No&lt;/em&gt;.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LOCAL_SOURCE_METADATA_DELTA_FINDER: Flag enabling the use of a local source for the metadata delta finder. Can take two values: Yes: Use a local source as defined by the parameter OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR; No: use the content PyCSW server as defined by the parameter: FORCED_PYCSW_URL.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;LOCAL_WRITER: Flag enabling to write the output locally or on the server.  Can take two values: Yes: Write the output locally as defined by the parameter:OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR; No: Write the output in the PyCSW server as defined by the parameter: FORCEDS_PYCSW_URL.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;METADATA_OVERWRITE: Enable the overwite of the PyCSW.  Can take two values: Yes: Overwrite the contentof the PyCSW; No: Do no overwrite the content of the PyCSW.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_OUT_WORKING_DIR: Root working directory used to define the following &lt;em&gt;private parameters&lt;/em&gt;:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;IN_CSV_LOOKUP_TABLES_DIR: Source directory of the root of the lookup table files. Defined as: \\LOOKUP_TABLES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;IN_GMD_XML_TEMPLATES_DIR: Source directory of the root XML templates. Defined as: \\XML_TEMPLATES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;INJSON_TEMPLATE_DIR: Source directory of the root JSON templates. Defined as: \\JSON_TEMPLATES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;LOG_FILE: Output log file. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\LOG\\QC.log&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_JSON_LOCAL_DIR: Source directory to output JSON files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\JSON_LOCAL&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XLS_NOTIFICATION: Source directory to output excel files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XLS&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_FAILED_DIR: Source directory to output failed XML files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XML_FAILED&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_LOCAL_DIR: Source directory to output &lt;em&gt;Local Source&lt;/em&gt; XML files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XML_LOCAL&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;OUT_XML_PASSED_DIR: Source directory to output passedXML files. Defined as: C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\\QC\\XML_PASSED&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;SAMPLE_SIZE: Number of features to process. Zero (0) means process all the features. A number &lt;em&gt;n&lt;/em&gt; greater than 0 means sample or process only the first &lt;em&gt;n&lt;/em&gt; features.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;URL_VALIDATION : Indicates to validate or not created URL. (Should be Yes for prod)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;VALIDATE_INSERT_PCT :Indicates to valide insert percentage. 75 % or less insert/update record  (Should be Yes for prod)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-02-27T16:25:54-05:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2026-02-27T16:25:53-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;QC_PROD.fmw&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;QC_PROD&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalRuns&quot;: 5, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;WORKSPACE&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:30-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:12:01-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;QC_PROJECTION_GEOEXTENTS_EXTRACTOR.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;QC_PROJECTION_GEOEXTENTS_EXTRACTOR&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:30-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:12:39-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;QC_WMS_URL_SETTER.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;QC_WMS_URL_SETTER&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This custom transformer identify the resources that contains WMS and/or ESRI RESTand test for broken service through an http call. If the service is broken it removes that service and adjust the distribution list.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;INPUT: The metadata records to process.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;FAULTY_URL_OUTPUT: The metadata records with broken URL.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;OUTPUT: The output metadata records.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;None&lt;/p&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:31-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:14:04-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;REMOVE_BROKEN_URL_WMS_ESRI_REST.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;REMOVE_BROKEN_URL_WMS_ESRI_REST&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This custom transformer validates the URL, the FORMAT and the NAME attributes of each list of the resources{} of the metadata records.  If the URL is missing this list is dropped. If the FORMAT is missing the value OTHER is added.  If the format is missing the value of the TITLE attribute is supplied.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;If there is no resources, feature is dropped&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;INPUT: Input metadata records toprocess&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;OUTPUT: The process output metdata records with resources validated&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;NONE&lt;/p&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:31-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:15:30-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;RESOURCES_VALIDATOR.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;RESOURCES_VALIDATOR&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This transformer removes all underscores from resources{}.name attributes.  Long compounded names joined by underscores in this field can cause display formatting issues when published to the FGP.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;INPUT: Input metadata records to process.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;DATA_OUTPUT: The process output metdata records.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;NONE&lt;/p&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:31-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:14:37-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;RESOURCE_NAME_UNDERSCORE_REMOVER.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;RESOURCE_NAME_UNDERSCORE_REMOVER&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This custom transformer sorts the record (feature) to be published based on the sector name.  The valid sector name is contained in a CSV file.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;INPUT: The input metadata records (features) to process.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;PUBLISHED_OUTPUT: The records (features) to be publihed in the FGP based on the sector name.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;UNPUBLISHED_OUTPUT: The records (features) not to be publihed in the FGP based on the sector name.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;UNMAPPED_OUTPUT: The records (features) for which the sector is not present (unmapped)  in the CSV file.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;FEATURE_TYPE: Name of the CSV file to read (without .csv extension);&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_CSV_LOOKUP_TABLES_DIR: Name of the directory path containing the CSV file to read;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;P-T_ABBR: Two letters abbreviation of the province or the territory.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:32-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:15:57-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;SECTOR_MAPPER_NG.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;SECTOR_MAPPER_NG&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:32-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-10-07T09:27:55-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;SocrataAPICaller.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;SocrataAPICaller&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:33-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-10-06T16:17:25-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;SocrataDateTimeConverter.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;SocrataDateTimeConverter&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:33-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-10-06T16:18:37-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;SocrataHashIDGenerator.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;SocrataHashIDGenerator&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:34-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:19:10-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;SOCRATA_ADDITIONAL_ACCESS_POINTS_RESOURCES_EXTRACTOR.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;SOCRATA_ADDITIONAL_ACCESS_POINTS_RESOURCES_EXTRACTOR&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:34-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:21:47-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;SOCRATA_ADVANCED_VIEW_EXTRACTOR.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;SOCRATA_ADVANCED_VIEW_EXTRACTOR&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:34-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:25:02-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;SOCRATA_ATTACHEMENTS_EXTRACTOR.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;SOCRATA_ATTACHEMENTS_EXTRACTOR&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:35-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:26:34-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;SOCRATA_BOUNDING_BOX_EXTRACTOR.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;SOCRATA_BOUNDING_BOX_EXTRACTOR&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:35-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:30:20-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;SOCRATA_INSIDE_DB_EXTRACTOR_NG.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;SOCRATA_INSIDE_DB_EXTRACTOR_NG&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:35-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:30:36-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;SOCRATA_METADATA_MERGER.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;SOCRATA_METADATA_MERGER&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This Custom Transformer read the content of a Socrata server.  All the information is read and all the information is transformed into FME attributes.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Input: One feature needed to start the reading of the Socrata server.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Output: One feature for each metadata record read from the Socrata server.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Domain: The url of the Socrata server.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:36-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:30:53-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;SOCRATA_READER_NG.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;SOCRATA_READER_NG&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:36-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:31:09-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;Spatial_extent_validator.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;Spatial_extent_validator&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This custom transformer attributes a spatial representation type to the input metadata records based on the list attribute resources{}.spatial_type.  The FME attribute resources{}.spatial_type can take one of the following values&lt;/p&gt; &lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt; - &amp;lt;empty value&amp;gt;  - a-grid  - b-vector  - c-textTable &lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt; &lt;p&gt;In order to set the spatial representation type.  The method count the number of occurences of each value except the &lt;empty-value&gt; or \&quot;\&quot;  value. It will set the spatial representation to the value that has the most count.  In case of  equality the a-grid has priority over b-vector and the latter has priority over c-textTable.  For the spatial representation we remove the \&quot;a-\&quot;,  \&quot;b-\&quot; or \&quot;c-\&quot; and only keep \&quot;grid\&quot;, \&quot;vector\&quot; or \&quot;textTable\&quot; that is set in the  FME attribute spatial_representation_type.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;DATA_INPUT: The input metadata records to process.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;DATA_OUTPUT_PASSED: The output metdata records for which the spatial representation type was successfully set.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;DATA_OUTPUT_FAILED: The output metdata records for which the spatial representation type was not successfully set.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;FEATURE_TYPE: Name of the CSV file to read (without .csv extension);&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_CSV_LOOKUP_TABLES_DIR: Name of the directory path containing the CSV file to read;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;P-T_ABBR: Two letters abbreviation of the province or the territory.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:37-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:31:28-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;SPATIAL_TYPE_MAPPER_NG.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;SPATIAL_TYPE_MAPPER_NG&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuPct&quot;: 37.600068496082876, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuTime&quot;: 8783, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgElapsedTime&quot;: 23359, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgPeakMemUsage&quot;: 80401066, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Ce workbench permet de synchroniser le dépôt CKAN avec des fichiers CKAN en format JSON pour une province données. Le workbench lit le contenu du fichier CKAN et vérifie que la date de création des fichiers est ultérieur à la date des fichiers lus dans le dépôt CKAN. Si la date est ultérieure, les fichiers sont chargés dans le dépôt CKAN sinon les fichiers ne sont pas chargés dans le dépôt CKAN. Si durant le processus de chargement une erreur (format ou contenu) est détecté le fichier n&apos;est pas chargé et une description détaillée des erreurs est fournis.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Aucun port d&apos;entrée&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;&lt;em&gt;Aucun port de sortie&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;CKAN_KEY: La clé &lt;em&gt;secrète&lt;/em&gt; CKAN pour accéder au dépôt de de données CKAN.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;ENV: L&apos;environnement CKAN pour lire et charger des données CKAN. Peut prendre deux valuers: OPENDATA-STAGING pour accéder à l&apos;environnement staging de CKAN; OPENDATA-PROD: pour accéder à l&apos;environnement de production de CKAN&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;P-T_ABBR: L&apos;abbréviation de deux lettres de la province à traiter (ex.: ON pour Ontario)&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;IN_OUT_WORKING_DIR: Le nom du répertoire de travail contenant les fichiers CKAN à charger. Ex.: si on inscrit \&quot;C:\\Data\\PT_Harvester\&quot; les fichiers CKAN doivent se trouver dans le répertoire: \&quot;C:\\DATA\\PT_HARVESTER\\xx\\JSON_LOCAL\&quot; ou \&quot;xx\&quot; est le code de deux lettres de la province.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-20T15:48:37-05:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:58:27-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;Synchronisation_CKAN.fmw&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;Synchronisation_CKAN&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalRuns&quot;: 6, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;WORKSPACE&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;steven-poulin&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:37-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:32:00-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;TEMPORAL_EXTENTS_MAPPER.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;TEMPORAL_EXTENTS_MAPPER&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;Ce custom transformer est utilisé pour vérifier si le nombre d&apos;entités traitées est acceptable. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;Si le nombre d&apos;entités n&apos;est pas respecté, le programme génère une erreur. &amp;lt;br/&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;Le custom ne génère pas d&apos;erreur si : &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;Seuil minimal &amp;lt;= Nombre d&apos;entités traitées &amp;lt;=Seuil maximal&amp;lt;br/&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;Documentation : &amp;lt;a href=\&quot;\\\\dfscitsh\\cits\\envcits\\applications\\cits\\pro\\doc\\TerminatorMinMax.doc\&quot;&amp;gt;TerminatorMinMax.doc&amp;lt;/a&amp;gt;&amp;lt;br/&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;Note : Les données entrantes ressortent intactes du transformer afin de pouvoir au besoin mettre&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;le transformer au milieu d&apos;une chaine de traitement, mais le transformer peut aussi être utilisé en fin&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;de traitement&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;h2&amp;gt;Paramètres : &amp;lt;/h2&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;p&amp;gt;Termination message  : &amp;lt;/p&amp;gt; &amp;lt;li/&amp;gt;Message d&apos;erreur à inscrire dans le log. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;li/&amp;gt;Le nombre d&apos;élément trouvé / nombre d&apos;élément attendu sera automatiquement ajouté au message&amp;lt;br/&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;Nombre minimal d&apos;entités :&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;li/&amp;gt;Nombre minimal d&apos;entité attendu. Si le nombre d&apos;entités trouvées  est plus petit (&amp;lt;) que le nombre attendu, le programme génère une erreur. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;li/&amp;gt;Mettre un chiffre ou utiliser * pour indiquer qu&apos;il n&apos;y a pas de minimum&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;li/&amp;gt;Toute valeur autre qu&apos;un nombre entier est traité comme * &amp;lt;br/&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;Nombre maximal d&apos;entités :&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;li/&amp;gt;Nombre maximal d&apos;entité attendu. Si le nombre d&apos;entités trouvées  est plus grand (&amp;gt;) que le nombre attendu, le programme génère une erreur.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;li/&amp;gt;Mettre un chiffre ou utiliser * pour indiquer qu&apos;il n&apos;y a pas de maximum &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;li/&amp;gt;Toute valeur autre qu&apos;un nombre entier est traité comme *&amp;lt;br/&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&amp;lt;br/&amp;gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:37-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-25T10:50:21-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;TerminatorMinMax.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;TerminatorMinMax&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;h2&gt;Description&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;p&gt;This transformer extracts a zip file to a temporary directory, returning the path in both Windows- and Unix-style. Using these paths, you can copy the files to a permanent location using a File Copy writer, or make further use of them in a FeatureReader, for example. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Details&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;p&gt;This custom transformer utilizes a FeatureReader with the Directory and File Pathnames format to extract the files within the input zip dataset to a temporary location. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;One feature for each file contained within the zip dataset is sent through the Output port with the attribute &lt;code&gt;path_windows&lt;/code&gt; and &lt;code&gt;path_unix&lt;/code&gt; containing the Windows- and Unix-style temporary file path respectively.&lt;/p&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:38-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2019-07-30T15:55:35-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;Unzipper.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;Unzipper&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuPct&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuTime&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgElapsedTime&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgPeakMemUsage&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-20T15:48:37-05:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:58:50-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;UploadGeoDCat2OSDP.fmw&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalRuns&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;WORKSPACE&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;steven-poulin&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;!DOCTYPE HTML PUBLIC \&quot;-//W3C//DTD HTML 4.0//EN\&quot; \&quot;http://www.w3.org/TR/REC-html40/strict.dtd\&quot;&gt; &lt;html&gt;&lt;head&gt;&lt;meta name=\&quot;qrichtext\&quot; content=\&quot;1\&quot; /&gt;&lt;style type=\&quot;text/css\&quot;&gt; p, li { white-space: pre-wrap; } &lt;/style&gt;&lt;/head&gt;&lt;body style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;MS Shell Dlg 2&apos;; font-size:7.8pt; font-weight:400; font-style:normal;\&quot;&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=\&quot; font-size:10pt; font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline;\&quot;&gt;Description &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-size:10pt; font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline;\&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul style=\&quot;margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; -qt-list-indent: 1;\&quot;&gt;&lt;li style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=\&quot; font-size:10pt;\&quot;&gt;This custom transformer substitutes the character &amp;quot;{&amp;quot; with the chatacters &amp;quot;%7B&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;}&amp;quot; with the chatacters &amp;quot;%7D&amp;quot; for the the resource list &amp;quot;resources{} for all the metadata records.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:1; text-indent:0px; font-size:10pt;\&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-size:10pt; font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline;\&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=\&quot; font-size:10pt; font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline;\&quot;&gt;Input Ports &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-size:10pt; font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline;\&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul style=\&quot;margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; -qt-list-indent: 1;\&quot;&gt;&lt;li style=\&quot; font-size:10pt; font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline;\&quot; style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=\&quot; text-decoration:none;\&quot;&gt;INPUT:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=\&quot; font-weight:400; text-decoration:none;\&quot;&gt; The input metadata records to process.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-size:10pt;\&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-size:10pt;\&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=\&quot; font-size:10pt; font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline;\&quot;&gt;Output Ports &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-size:10pt; font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline;\&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul style=\&quot;margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; -qt-list-indent: 1;\&quot;&gt;&lt;li style=\&quot; font-size:10pt; font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline;\&quot; style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=\&quot; text-decoration:none;\&quot;&gt;DATA_OUTPUT: &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span style=\&quot; font-weight:400; text-decoration:none;\&quot;&gt;The output metadata records&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-size:10pt; font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline;\&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-size:10pt; font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline;\&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=\&quot; font-size:10pt; font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline;\&quot;&gt;Parameters &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-size:10pt; font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline;\&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul style=\&quot;margin-top: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; margin-right: 0px; -qt-list-indent: 1;\&quot;&gt;&lt;li style=\&quot; font-size:10pt; font-weight:600; text-decoration: underline;\&quot; style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=\&quot; font-style:italic; text-decoration:none;\&quot;&gt;None&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/body&gt;&lt;/html&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:38-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:33:48-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;URL_CHARACTER_ENCODER.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;URL_CHARACTER_ENCODER&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:38-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:34:20-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;URL_HTTPS_MAKER.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;URL_HTTPS_MAKER&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:39-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:34:55-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;URL_HTTPS_MAKER_NO_RESOURCES.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;URL_HTTPS_MAKER_NO_RESOURCES&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuPct&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuTime&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgElapsedTime&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgPeakMemUsage&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;h1&gt;Description:&lt;/h1&gt; &lt;p&gt;Programme développé dans le cadre du projet de fédération de données. Ce programme a pour but de valider la sycnhronisation de contenu entre les différentes composantes du processus. Les validations se font autant pour le contenu géo que non Géo. Le processus valide à la fois la présence des données dans les différentes composantes ainsi que la date de mise jour permettant ainsi de détecter les problèmes d\&quot;ajout/suppression de métadonnées ainsi que les mises à jour.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Validation du contenu non geo:&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;p&gt;Les données non geo se retrouvent à deux endrroits pour la fédération de données. Le répertoire JSON_LOCAL (appelé disque) de chaque P/T sur la machine FME Server où sont traitées les données ainsi que le portail Open Data (appelé CKAN où sont publiées les données Le programme comparre ces 2 dépôts et peut identifier 3 types d&apos;erreurs:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;Problème de mise à jour de contenu de CKAN.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Les métadonnées sont présentes à la fois sur le disque et dans CKAN mais la date de mise à jour dans CKAN est plus vieille que celle des fichiers sur le disque. Il y a donc un problème de mise àj jour des données. Lorsqu&apos;une erreur de ce type est identifiée, elle est écrite dans &lt;strong&gt;NG-ProblemeDate&lt;/strong&gt;. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;Problème d&apos;ajout de métadonné. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Pour identifier cette erreur, on compare la date federated_date_modified (DISQUE) avec modified_date (CKAN) avec&#9;La métadonnée a été écrite sur le DISQUE mains n&apos;a pas été publié dans CKAN.  Lorsqu&apos;une erreur de ce type est identifiée, elle est écrite dans &lt;strong&gt;NG-DisquePasCKAN&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;Problème de suppresion de métadonnée. &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;La métadonnée a été supprimé du DISQUE mais l&apos;action n&apos;a pas percollé au niveau de CKAN.  Lorsqu&apos;une erreur de ce type est identifiée, elle est écrite dans &lt;strong&gt;NG-CkanPasDisque&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;h2&gt;Validation du contenu géo&lt;/h2&gt; &lt;p&gt;La validation pour la partie Géo est plus complexe que le non géo car les métadonnées se retrouvent à 3 endroits soit le #1 pycsw (appelé Pycsw), #2  le catalogue externe de la PGF (appelé CatExt) et#3  OpenData  (appelé CKAN). Tout comme pour le non géo, on retrouve des problèmes de mises à jours de métadonnées et des problèmes d&apos;ajout/supresion&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;Problème de mise à jour de métadonnées dans OpenData: &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;La métadonnée présente  dans Open Data n&apos;est pas à jour par rapport au contenu du catalogue externe de la PGF. La date de modification de la donnée dans OpenData est plus veille que la date de transaction dans le catalogue externe . Lorsqu&apos;une erreur de ce type est identifiée, elle est écrite dans &lt;strong&gt;G-ProbDateCatExtCKAN&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;Problème d\&quot;ajout de métadonnées dans OpenData:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;La métadonnée est présente dans le catalgoue externe de la PGF mais absent d&apos;OpenData. Lorsqu&apos;une erreur de ce type est identifiée, elle est écrite dans &lt;strong&gt;G-CatExtPasCkan&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;Problème de suppresion de métadonnées dans OpenData:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;La métaonnée n&apos;existe pas dans le catalgoue externe mais est toujours présente dans Open Data. Lorsqu&apos;une erreur de ce type est identifiée, elle est écrite dans  &lt;strong&gt;G-CkanPasCatExt&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;Problème de mise à jour du catalogue externe:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;La métadonnée présente  dans catalogue externe  n&apos;est pas à jour par rapport au contenu du pycsw  La date de transaction dans le catalgoue est plus veille que le time stamp de création de la métadonnée dans le PyCSW. Lorsqu&apos;une erreur de ce type est identifiée, elle est écrite dans &lt;strong&gt;G-ProbDate-CatExtPycsw&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;Problème d\&quot;ajout de métadonnées dans le catalogue externe:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;La métadonnée est présente dans le pycsw mais absente du catalogue externe. Lorsqu&apos;une erreur de ce type est identifiée, elle est écrite dans &lt;strong&gt;G-PycswPasCatExt&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt; &lt;p&gt;Problème de suppresion de métadonnées dans le catalogue externe:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;La métaonnée n&apos;existe pas dans le pycsw  mais est toujours présente dansle catalogue externe. Lorsqu&apos;une erreur de ce type est identifiée, elle est écrite dans  &lt;strong&gt;G-CatExtPasPycsw&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-20T15:48:39-05:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:59:48-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;WatchDog_Publication.fmw&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;WatchDog_Publication&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalRuns&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;WORKSPACE&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;steven-poulin&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This transformer creates default values (add protocol attribute) in the resources{} list required for transferOptions in the XML Template; and creates an additional resources{} list entry that is required for the second language WMS and ESRI REST format types.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;INPUT: Input metadata records to process&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;OUTPUT: The process output metadata records&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;None&lt;/p&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:40-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-19T12:39:35-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;WMS_REST_LANGUAGE_FORMATTER.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;WMS_REST_LANGUAGE_FORMATTER&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This custom transformer is translating the input spatial metadata records into the XML HNAP model.  The rules on how to map the input features attributes (records) into the HNAP attributes are stored in the XML configuration file. The XML templates used to create the output HNAP XML file are supplied with the input published parameters of the custom transformers.  The mapping into XML file is done with FME XML Templater transformer.  If the publish parameter LOCAL_WRITER is set to NO, the custom tranformer will insert or update the records in thePyCSW.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;Note: Because of a problem with the PyCSW server, record update are done in 2 steps: first the record is deleted; secondly the record is inserted.&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Input Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;Input: The input metadata records to translate and write into the XML HNAP model.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Output Ports &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;INSERT_PASSED: The HNAP metdata records that are inserted (new records)&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;UPDATE_PASSED: The HNAP metdata records that area updated (edited records)&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;INSERT_FAILED: The HNAP metdata records that are inserted (new records) but which failed the PyCSW insert process&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;UPDATE_FAILED: The HNAP metdata records that are updated (edited records) but which failed the PyCSW update process&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;LOCAL: All HNAP metadata records (insert and iupdate) if LOCAL_WRITER (published parameter) is set to YES&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;InvalidMetadata: HNAP metadata records that failed a validation&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Parameters &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;TEMPLATE_GMD_CITERESPONSIBILITYPARTY: File system address containing the template section of the CITERESPONSABILITYPARTY of the HNAP model&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;TEMPLATE_GMD_CONTACT: File system address containing the template section of the CONTACT of the HNAP model&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;TEMPLATE_GMD_DISTRIBUTIONFORMAT: File system address containing the template section of the DISTRIBUTIONFORMAT of the HNAP model&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;TEMPLATE_GMD_KEYWORDS: File system address containing the template section of the KEYWORDS of the HNAP model&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;TEMPLATE_GMD_MDMETADATA: File system address containing the METADATA root template of the HNAP model&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;TEMPLATE_GMD_REFERENCESYSTEMINFO: File system address containing the template section of the REFERENCESYSTEMINFO of the HNAP model&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;TEMPLATE_GMD_RESOURCESMAINTENANCE: File system address containing the template section of the RESOURCEMAINTENANCE of the HNAP model&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;TEMPLATE_GMD_TOPICCATEGORY: File system address containing the template section of the TOPICCATEGORY of the HNAP model&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;TEMPLATE_GMD_TRANSFEROPTION: File system address containing the template section of the TRANSFEROPTION of the HNAP model&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;LOCAL_WRITER: Flag indicating if the output records must be written or not to the PyCSW server. YES: Write to the PyCSW server; NO: Do not write to the PyCSW server.&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:41-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:42:04-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;XML_PUBLISHER_NG.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;XML_PUBLISHER_NG&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:42-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:45:27-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;yt_catalogue_reader_NG.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;yt_catalogue_reader_NG&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Description &lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;p&gt;This transformer uses thoses attributes:&lt;/p&gt; &lt;ul&gt; &lt;li&gt;author_email&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;contact&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;contact_role&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;default_contact_email&lt;/li&gt; &lt;li&gt;default_contact_role&lt;/li&gt; &lt;/ul&gt; &lt;p&gt;It adjust the format of thoses attributes, set default values if needed for author_email and contact_role and output a list contact{}.role and contact{}.email. &lt;/p&gt;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:42-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:44:44-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;YT_CONTACTS_MERGER.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;YT_CONTACTS_MERGER&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:43-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:44:07-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;YT_CUSTOM_CATALOGUE_READER.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;YT_CUSTOM_CATALOGUE_READER&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:43-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2025-11-04T13:41:04-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;YT_DATE_FORMATTER.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;YT_DATE_FORMATTER&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuPct&quot;: 81.06605672106613, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgCpuTime&quot;: 669497, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgElapsedTime&quot;: 825866, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;avgPeakMemUsage&quot;: 703751782, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-02-23T11:18:06-05:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2026-02-23T11:18:05-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;YT_PROD.fmw&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalRuns&quot;: 10, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;WORKSPACE&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;}, &#9;&#9;{ &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;description&quot;: &quot;&lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;Extracts files archived in a zip file, and then outputs features for every extracted file and directory.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;Each resulting feature has two attributes storing full path string of an extracted file/directory - &lt;/span&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; color:#aa0000;\&quot;&gt;\&quot;path_unix\&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;(UNIX style) and &lt;/span&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; color:#aa0000;\&quot;&gt;\&quot;path_windows\&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;(Windows style), and also has an attribute that indicates the depth of the file/directory in the extracted directory hierarchy - &lt;/span&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; color:#aa0000;\&quot;&gt;\&quot;path_depth\&quot; &lt;/span&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;(integer starting from 1).&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;The features containing file path will be output through the File port, and the features containing directory path will be output through the Directory port. &lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;All the extracted files will be saved into a subfolder under the folder specified with the \&quot;Destination Root Folder\&quot; parameter. The subfolder name will be the same as the source zip file name without extension. For example, if the source zip file name is &lt;/span&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; color:#aa0000;\&quot;&gt;\&quot;data.zip\&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;and the specified root folder path is &lt;/span&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; color:#aa0000;\&quot;&gt;\&quot;C:\\root\&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;, extracted files will be saved into &lt;/span&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; color:#aa0000;\&quot;&gt;\&quot;C:\\root\\data\&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;If the same name folder exists under the specified root folder, a number will be added to the destination subfolder name as suffix to differentiate from the existing folder, by default. e.g. &lt;/span&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; color:#aa0000;\&quot;&gt;\&quot;C:\\root\\data_1\&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;, &lt;/span&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; color:#aa0000;\&quot;&gt;\&quot;C:\\root\\data_2\&quot;&lt;/span&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;, and so on. &lt;/span&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; font-size:medium; color:#000000;\&quot;&gt;If you set \&quot;Yes\&quot; to the \&quot;Replace Existing Destination Subfolder\&quot; parameter, the existing subfolder and all files within it will be removed, and then the destination subfolder will be created newly.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;; font-size:medium; color:#000000;\&quot;&gt;By default, this transformer will NOT unzip zip files that are archived (nested) in the source zip file. If you set \&quot;Yes\&quot; to the \&quot;Unzip Nested Zip Files Recursively\&quot; parameter, this transformer unzips all the nested zip files recursively.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;All attributes of the input feature will be propagated to the output features, but the geometry and coordinate system will not be preserved.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;If the specified source zip file or destination root folder is invalid, the input feature will be output through the &amp;lt;Rejected&amp;gt; port.&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot;-qt-paragraph-type:empty; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;br/&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &lt;p style=\&quot; margin-top:0px; margin-bottom:0px; margin-left:0px; margin-right:0px; -qt-block-indent:0; text-indent:0px;\&quot;&gt;&#9; &lt;span style=\&quot; font-family:&apos;Verdana&apos;;\&quot;&gt;Note: The Unzipper (FME Hub) can also be used to unzip a zip file. The ZipExtractor may be useful if you need to specify the destination root folder and/or to unzip nested zip file(s).&lt;/span&gt; &lt;/p&gt; &quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;fileCount&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastPublishDate&quot;: &quot;2026-03-10T14:49:43-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;lastSaveDate&quot;: &quot;2020-01-13T16:46:42-04:00&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;name&quot;: &quot;ZipExtractor.fmx&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;repositoryName&quot;: &quot;PT_Harvester&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;title&quot;: &quot;ZipExtractor&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;totalFileSize&quot;: 0, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;type&quot;: &quot;CUSTOMTRANSFORM&quot;, &#9;&#9;&#9;&quot;userName&quot;: &quot;mark-lague&quot; &#9;&#9;} &#9;], &#9;&quot;limit&quot;: -1, &#9;&quot;offset&quot;: -1, &#9;&quot;totalCount&quot;: 97 } "/>
